<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>Discussion groups for Developmental Education</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BACKGROUND="../Gifs/yellow_rock.gif"><H1><CENTER>Welcome to the Whole Language<BR>College Reading Discussion Groups page<A HREF="../../Whole_Language.html#anchor98827"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/cynus2.GIF" WIDTH="203" HEIGHT="92" ALIGN="TOP" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></CENTER></H1><P><CENTER><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="467" HEIGHT="10" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"><BR><BR><ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE BORDER=3 WIDTH="80%" HEIGHT="5" CELLPADDING=3 CELLSPACING=3><TR><TH><A HREF="#anchor158809">Preview</A></TH><TH><A HREF="#anchor279347">How to subscribe</A></TH> <TH><A HREF="#anchor139800">DiscussionGroups</A></TH> </TR> </TABLE></CENTER><H1><CENTER><HR><A NAME="anchor158809"></A>Preview</CENTER></H1><DL>  <DT>This page describes <A HREF="#anchor279347">how to subscribe</A> tovarious electronic discussion groups that discuss developmental education.Then, it provides a listing of the <A HREF="#anchor139800">discussion groups</A>.If you find others that are not listed here or if the address is incorrect,please e-mail the webmaster and he/she will correct this listing. Enjoy.<HR></DL><H1><CENTER><A NAME="anchor279347"></A>E-mail Discussion Groups</CENTER></H1>This is a list of useful discussion groups for developmental educators.To join these discussion groups, you send a message to a computer program(either Majordomo or Listserv). To join a group that uses the <B>LISTSERV</B>server, follow these directions. Note this first example is to subscribeto the LRNASST discussion group, an excellent discussion group on learningassistance at the college level. Notice, we would send an e-mail messageto the LISTSERV program (which also happens to be the name of the computerat the University of Arizona). In the Subject: line, we leave blank, sincethe computer program doesn't recognize a message anyway. Then in the bodyof the message, simply enter the SUBSCRIBE command (upper or lower case)followed by your first name and your last name. The computer program recognizesyour e-mail address from the header in your message. In a few hours or afew days, you will receive a message that you are subscribed and directionsfor using the discussion group. Keep these for future reference. Especiallythe <B>DIGEST</B> function which allows you to receive only one messagecontaining a reference to all the messages for that day. <BR><BR>For example, if I were to subscribe to this <A NAME="anchor313278"></A>LRNASSTgroup I would send the following e-mail message. Note this is specific tomy Digital VAX mainframe on my campus. Your mail system may work differently.<BR><BR><DD>$: mail <BR><DD>MAIL&gt;: send <BR><DD>TO: IN%&quot;listserv@listserv.arizona.edu&quot; <DD>(note no spacesin the address) <BR><DD>SUBJ:<DD> (press return, no subject line is necessary) <BR><DD>subscribe LRNASST David Caverly <BR><BR><DD>cnt-z <DD>(zend off the message by pressing control-z at the same time)<BR><BR><BR>Now when I want to <B>UNSUBSCRIBE</B>, I have to send a message to the samecomputer program, LISTSERV, telling it I want to unsubscribe to the discussiongroup. For example, I would send this message to unsubscribe to the LRNASSTgroup: <BR><BR><DD>$: mail <BR><DD>MAIL&gt;: send <BR><DD>TO: IN%&quot;listserv@listserv.arizona.edu&quot;<DD>(note no spacesin the address) <BR><DD>SUBJ:<DD>(press return, no subject line is necessary) <BR><DD>unsubscribe<DD>(note this is all the message in the body)<BR><BR><DD>cnt-z (zend off the message by pressing control-z at the same time)<BR><BR><BR>To join a group that uses the <B>Majordomo</B> server, follow these directions.While they are like the LISTSERV, they are slightly different. For example,to join an Community College ESL discussion group, I would:<BR><BR><DD>$: mail <BR><DD>MAIL&gt;: send <BR><DD>TO: IN%&quot;majordomo@hcc.hawaii.edu&quot; <DD>(note no spaces in theaddress) <BR><DD>SUBJ: <DD><DD>(press return, no subject line is necessary) <BR><DD>subscribe ESLCC <DD>(where &quot;ESLCC&quot; is the desired list) <BR><BR><DD>cnt-z <DD>(zend off the message by pressing control-z at the same time)<BR><BR>Most other discussion groups have subscription procedures like Majordomo.<BR><P><CENTER><HR></CENTER><H1><CENTER><A NAME="anchor139800"></A>Discussion Groups</CENTER></H1><H4>Two useful sources for finding discussion groups are: <BR><BR><A HREF="http://www.oak-ridge.com/ierdrep1.html">Dr. E's Eclectic Compendiumof Electronic Resources for Adult/Distance Education</A><BR><BR>Diane Kovac's <A HREF="gopher://gopher.usask.ca:70/00/Computing/Internet%20Information/Directory%20of%20Scholarly%20Electronic%20Conferences/Education">Directoryof Scholarly and Professsional E-conferences<BR><BR></A>Those I have found useful include:</H4><H4><CENTER><ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE BORDER=3 WIDTH="80%" HEIGHT="5" CELLPADDING=3 CELLSPACING=3><TR><TH>Name</TH><TH>Description</TH> <TH>Subscription Address</TH><ALIGN=LEFT> </TR><TR><TD></CENTER></H4><DL>  <DT>AAUA-L</TD> <TD>American Association of University Administrators</TD><TD></DL><P><CENTER>listserv@ubvm.cc.buffalo.edu</TD> <TR> <TD> ACADV</TD><TD> AcademicAdvising services in higher ed</TD><TD> listserv@vm1.nodak.edu</TD> </TR><TR> <TD> ADLTED-L</TD> <TD>Canadian-based adult education list</TD> <TD>listserv@ureginal.uregina.ca</TD></TR> <TR> <TD> ADJUNCT </TD><TD> National Adjunct Faculty Guild </TD><TD>listserv@vm1.nodak.edu</TD> </TR> <TR> <TD> AEDNET</TD> <TD>Adult EducationalDiscussion list</TD> <TD>aednet@pulsar.acast.nova.edu</TD> </TR> <TR> <TD>AERA</TD> <TD>American Educational Research Association</TD> <TD>listserv@asuvm.inre.asu.edu</TD></TR> <TR> <TD> AFAM-L</TD> <TD>Listserv discussion about AfroAmerican students</TD><TD>LISTSERV@uscmvb.bitnet</TD> </TR> <TR> <TD> AI-ED</TD> <TD>ArtificialIntelligence discussion list</TD> <TD>ai-ed-request@sun.com</TD> </