<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>Degree Outline</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><BR><BR><IMG SRC="Images/doimg1.gif" WIDTH="490" HEIGHT="181" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR><BR><A HREF="DEVGRP">Home |</A><A HREF="Degreeout.html"> </A><A HREF="deved1.html">Missionand History </A><A HREF="Degreeout.html">|</A><A HREF="admcrit.html">AdmissionsCriteria |</A> <A HREF="finsup.html">Financial Support |</A> <A HREF="news.html">News|</A> <A HREF="Profemp.html">Professional/Employment Opportunity |</A> <A HREF="faculty.html">Faculty|</A> <A HREF="studdir.html">Student Directory |</A> <A HREF="#anchor146258"><BR><BR>MINOR </A>| <A HREF="#anchor149418">CAS</A> | <A HREF="#anchor161279">THESIS</A>| <A HREF="#anchor142366">INTERNSHIP</A> |<BR><BR><BR><B>The M.A. in Developmental and Adult Education</B> is a thirty-nine hourprogram, including thesis, which provides the expertise and experience tosupervise developmental and remedial education programs in a variety ofsettings such as junior/community colleges, vocational/technical schools,universities, adult literacy programs, and private industry. <BR><BR>Required coursework emphasizes developmental and adult education theoryand practice; special characteristics and needs of underprepared learners;program design, management, and evaluation; grant proposal preparation;research methodology; and teaching and learning strategies for reading,writing, and mathematics. A supervised internship practicum is also required.<BR><BR>Required Courses:<BR><BR>EDP 5375 The Underprepared Learner in American Postsecondary Education<BR>EDP 5365 The Administration of Developmental and Adult Education<BR>EDP 5371 Teaching Learning Strategies and Critical Thinking<BR>EDP 5320 Teaching Basic Writing<BR>CI 5320 Advanced Instructional Technology<BR>RDG 5395 Teaching Reading to Adults and Older Students<BR>Math 5304 Topics in Mathematics for the Secondary Teacher<BR>PE 5346 Literature and Research<BR>EDP 5389 Internship Practicum<BR>EDP 5399A Thesis<BR>EDP 5399B Thesis<BR><A NAME="anchor137676"></A><BR>Electives (choose two):<BR><BR>(Other electives may be selected in consultation with advisor.)<BR>SOCI 5370 Seminar in Multicultural Relations<BR>EDA 5392 The Community Junior College (Administration)<BR>EDA 5393 Community Junior College Curriculum<BR>EDA 5394 Teaching in the Junior Community College<BR><B><BR><BR>The <A HREF="#anchor137676">Mi</A></B><A NAME="anchor146258"></A><A NAME="anchor134414"></A><B><A HREF="#anchor137676">nor</A> in Developmental andAdult Education</B> consists of fifteen hours taken in conjunction witha Master of Education in Reading Education, English, or Mathematics. TheMinor provides the expertise and experience to teach in a variety of developmentaland remedial settings such as junior/community colleges, vocational/technicalschools, universities, and private industry.<BR><BR>Required coursework emphasizes developmental and adult education theoryand practice; program design, management, and evaluation; grant proposalpreparation; the special characteristics and needs of underprepared learners;and teaching and learning strategies for reading, writing, and mathematics.A supervised practicum is also required.<BR><A NAME="anchor153355"></A><BR>Required Courses:<BR><BR>EDP 5375 The Underprepared Learner in American Postsecondary Education<BR>EDP 5365 The Administration of Developmental Education<BR>EDP 5371 Teaching Learning Strategies and Critical Thinking<BR>EDP 5320 Teaching Basic Writers<BR>EDP 5389 Internship Practicum<BR><A NAME="anchor149418"></A><BR><BR><B><A HREF="#anchor149418">The Certificate of Advanced Study </A>(C.A.S.)in Developmental and Adult <BR>Education</B> is appropriate for professionals who already possess an advanceddegree and wish to <BR>acquire additional academic background relevant to teaching underpreparedstudents.  Required courses are the same as those required for the minorin Developmental and Adult Education.<BR><BR><B><A HREF="#anchor161279">Thesis Handbook and Guide</A></B><BR><BR><B>Southwest Texas State University Thesis Handbook</B><BR><BR>Developmental and Adult Education majors working on the master's thesisneed to pick up the SWT Thesis Handbook from the Graduate School officelocated at J C Kellam Blg. Rm. 280. The Thesis Handbook contains step-by-stepprocedures for writing a thesis. Also, the graduate student will be underthe guidance of a thesis committee. The committee will consist of two graduatefaculty members for the major department and one for a minor department.Before starting the thesis, a thesis ideas folder should be kept to aidin the development of ideas and keeping track of information as it comesavailable. The folder could include notes, references, journals, reflections,<BR>and <A NAME="anchor142366"></A>course assignments that relate to the thesis.<BR><BR><B>Developmental and Adult Education Program Thesis Guide<BR></B><BR>A Developmental and Adult Education Program thesis guide is in the processof being produced. Look for an announcement of its availability in the comingweeks.<BR><BR><B><A HREF="#anchor142366">Internship</A></B><BR><BR>One of the requirements for a major, minor or C.A.S. in Developmental andAdult Education is a supervised internship practicum. Dr. Lyman suggeststhat you keep an ideas folder as you go through your coursework to recordinternship possibilities. The internship packet can be picked up in theDevelopmental and Adult Education office in room 4002-1 of the Educationbuilding. See Dr. Lyman for more information about the internship practicum.<BR><BR>Any student who plans to begin an internship in Summer II or Fall 1996 mustsee Dr. Lyman before registering for approval of internship plans and toremove holds on registration for internship.<BR><BR><A HREF="DEVGRP">Home |</A><A HREF="Degreeout.html"> </A><A HREF="deved1.html">Missionand History </A><A HREF="Degreeout.html">|</A><A HREF="admcrit.html">AdmissionsCriteria |</A> <A HREF="finsup.html">Financial Support |</A> <A HREF="news.html">News|</A> <A HREF="Profemp.html">Professional/Employment Opportunity |</A> <A HREF="faculty.html">Faculty|</A> <A HREF="studdir.html">Student Directory |</A> </BODY></HTML>
