<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>Admissions Criteria</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><IMG SRC="Images/image3.gif" WIDTH="442" HEIGHT="162" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR><BR><A HREF="DEVGRP">Home |</A> <A HREF="deved1.html">Mission and History |</A><A HREF="Degreeout.html">Degree Outline |</A> <A HREF="finsup.html">FinancialSupport |</A> <A HREF="news.html">News |</A> <A HREF="Profemp.html">Professional/EmploymentOpportunity |</A> <A HREF="faculty.html">Faculty |</A> <A HREF="studdir.html">StudentDirectory |</A> <B><BR><BR>Requirement for Admission to M.A. Program<BR><BR></B>1. Bachelor's degree from an accredited institution.<BR><BR>2. One of the following, Graduate Record Exam (GRE) / grade point average(GPA)<BR>combinations: <BR>1000 GRE with 2.75 GPA for last 60 undergraduate hours<BR>950 GRE with 2.76-3.0 for the last 60 undergraduate hours<BR>900 GRE with 3.01+ for last 60 undergraduate hours<BR><BR>3. Application form on file in the Department of Educational Administrationand <BR>Psychological Services (EAPS).<BR><BR>4. Writing sample as specified on the last page of the application submittedto EAPS.<BR><BR>5. Transcripts of all previous undergraduate and graduate work submittedto EAPS.<BR><BR>6. Interview with EAPS faculty committee. Telephone (512) 245-2650 to schedule.<BR><BR>7. Application for admission to the Graduate School at Southwest Texas State<BR>University. <B>Note:</B> Application to the Graduate School does not guarantee<BR>admission to the M.A. program in Developmental Education.<BR><BR><B>Requirements for the Minor in Developmental Education</B><BR><BR>1. Admission to the M.Ed. program in reading education, English, or mathematics.<BR><BR>2. Approval of degree outline proposal by Developmental and Adult Educationgraduate <BR>advisor as well as major advisor.<BR><BR>3. Application form on file in the Department of Educational Administrationand <BR>Psychological Services (EAPS).<BR><BR>4. Transcripts of all previous undergraduate and graduate work submittedto EAPS.<BR><BR>5. Interview with EAPS faculty committee. Telephone (512) 245-2650 to schedule.<BR><BR><BR><BR><A HREF="DEVGRP">Home |</A> <A HREF="deved1.html">Mission and History |</A><A HREF="Degreeout.html">Degree Outline |</A> <A HREF="finsup.html">FinancialSupport |</A> <A HREF="news.html">News |</A> <A HREF="Profemp.html">Professional/EmploymentOpportunity |</A> <A HREF="faculty.html">Faculty |</A> <A HREF="studdir.html">StudentDirectory |</A> </BODY></HTML>
