<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>Financial Support</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><IMG SRC="Images/sdimg3.gif" WIDTH="472" HEIGHT="193" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR><BR><A HREF="DEVGRP">Home |</A> <A HREF="deved1.html">Mission and History |</A><A HREF="Degreeout.html">Degree Outline | </A><A HREF="admcrit.html">AdmissionsCriteria |</A> <A HREF="news.html">News |</A> <A HREF="Profemp.html">Professional/EmploymentOpportunity |</A> <A HREF="faculty.html">Faculty |</A> <A HREF="studdir.html">StudentDirectory |</A> <BR><BR><BR><A HREF="#anchor977875">Graduate School Scholars Program</A> | <A HREF="#anchor984845">SWTGraduate Minority Scholarships </A>|<BR><A NAME="anchor977875"></A><BR><B>Graduate Assistantship Positions</B> <BR><BR>Graduate assistantships are available for students majoring in programsin the Department of Educational Administration and Psychological Services(EAPS). Pick up the application forms from the departmental office.<BR><BR>Minimum requirements include having completed a minimum a) 12 hours of courseworkin the Developmental and Adult Education program, b) GPA of 3.5 for 12 ormore hours of Developmental Education program courses, and c) 900 on theGRE (Quantitative + Verbal).<BR><BR>Graduate assistants work 10 hours per week and earn $362.00 per month. Flexiblehours are required.<BR><BR><BR><A NAME="anchor981211"></A><BR><B><A HREF="#anchor981211">Graduate School Scholars Program</A></B><BR><BR>Scholarships up to $2100 per year (awarded in $700 increments per semester)will be awarded competitively each year by the Dean of the Graduate School.Scholarship may be renewed for a second year with the same competitive reviewas those applying for the first time.<BR><BR>Eligibility Requirements:<BR>A minimum 3.75 grade point average for the last sixty hours of the firstbachelor's degree is required for scholars consideration. Post graduatecourse work is not considered.<BR>Applicants must be unconditionally accepted to a SWT graduate degree program.Applications and admission information can be obtained from the GraduateSchool Office located in the J.C. Kellam Building, Room 280 or by calling512-245-2581.<BR><BR>Graduate School Scholars Program scholarship recipients must be continuouslyenrolled in a minimum of six semester hours of course work leading to thedegree each semester of the award and remain in good standing to be eligiblefor future semesters.<BR><BR>Application Process<BR>To apply for the SWT Graduate School Scholars Program scholarship, applicantsmust submit an application packet with the following information:<BR>&gt; An information page which includes applicant's full name, social securitynumber, permanent address and telephone, and program of study.<BR>&gt; A current resume.<BR>&gt; An essay of 500 words or less stating how graduate education will enablethe applicant to achieve their personal and/or professional goals.<BR>&gt; Three letters of recommendation from individuals familiar with theapplicant's academic background and ability (sent directly to the applicant).<BR><BR>The applicant should mail the entire application packet, including informationpage, resume, essay, and three letters of recommendation, to:<BR><BR>Southwest Texas State University<BR>The Graduate School<BR>601 University Drive<BR>San Marcos, Texas 78666-4605<BR><BR>The applicant may also deliver the entire application packet to the GraduateOffice located in suite 280 of the J.C. Kellam building at Southwest TexasState University.<BR>The entire application packet must be received in the Southwest Texas StateUniversity Graduate Office no later than July 1st. <BR><A NAME="anchor984845"></A><BR><B><A HREF="#anchor984845">SWT Graduate Minority Scholarships</A></B><BR><BR>Annual scholarships of $1500 (awarded in $500 increments per semester) willbe given each fall by the Office of the Graduate School. Recipient mustbe enrolled in a minimum of 6 hours and in good academic standing duringeach semester in which the scholarship is awarded. Scholarship may be renewablefor a second year. Applicant must reapply each year. <BR><BR>Selection Criteria<BR>The applicant must be a qualified minority applicant, i.e. American Indian,Alaskan Native, Black, Hispanic, Pacific Islander, or other ethnic groupthat has been traditionally under represented in graduate education andmust be a United States citizen.<BR><BR>Application Process<BR>&gt; Be unconditionally accepted to a SWT graduate degree program.<BR>&gt; Complete the attached application form and return to the Office ofthe Graduate School.<BR>&gt; Solicit 3 letters of recommendation. Letters should be sent to:<BR>Chair, Graduate Minority Scholarship Committee<BR>The Graduate School<BR>Southwest Texas State University<BR>601 University Drive<BR>San Marcos, Texas 78666-4605<BR>Letters should come from individuals familiar with your scholastic and/orwork <BR>experience. These letters should describe your intellectual promise andleadership.<BR>&gt; Submit an essay of 500 words or less stating ways the scholarship willenable you to achieve your graduate degree at SWT. Inclue in your essaya brief description of your career goals.<BR>&gt; Submit a current resume.<BR>&gt; Submit the application form and the above information to the Officeof the <BR>Graduate School at SWT by February 1. <BR><BR><BR>For more information, see the SWT Financial Aid page at:<BR><A HREF="http://www.swt.edu/SWTexan/studentservices.html#finaid">http://www.swt.edu/SWTexan/studentservices.html#finaid</A><BR><BR><A HREF="DEVGRP">Home |</A> <A HREF="deved1.html">Mission and History |</A><A HREF="Degreeout.html">Degree Outline | </A><A HREF="admcrit.html">AdmissionsCriteria |</A> <A HREF="news.html">News |</A> <A HREF="Profemp.html">Professional/EmploymentOpportunity |</A> <A HREF="faculty.html">Faculty |</A> <A HREF="studdir.html">StudentDirectory |</A> <BR><BR></BODY>