IS COMMITTEES CHAIRED: PROPOSALS APPROVED, IN PROGRESS<BR>Archield, A. The relationship between community college students' criticalthinking skills and writing course achievement. Proposal approved May 1996.<BR><BR>Guzman, S. L. The effect of an Upward Bound Program on retention among minoritystudents in post-secondary education. Proposal approved May 1996.<BR><BR>Ho, Y. H. A study of students' perceptions of reasons for leaving schoolbefore completion. Proposal approved December 1995.<BR><BR>Lickteig, C. Using computer mediated instruction as a training tool in business.Proposal approved September 1995.<BR><BR>Robinson, S. Course completion in a freshman level English Composition Iclass and the use of an in-class tutor. Proposal approved May 1996.<BR><BR>Wendt, K. Current trends in Texas alternative education. Proposal approvedNovember 1995.<BR>PAPERS PRESENTED AT PROFESSIONAL MEETINGS<BR>Payne, E.M., Stedman, D., Hoffman, V., Lyman, B., Wooley, J., &amp; Ashlock,S. (1996, March 13). Using the consortium model to address statewide literacyneeds. Panel presented at the 1996 World Conference on Literacy, Philadelphia,PA.<BR><BR>Lyman, B., &amp; Payne, E.M. (1996, March 1). New populations in developmentaleducation: Are we prepared to address their needs? Paper presented at theannual meeting of the National Association for Developmental Education,Little Rock, AK.<BR><BR>Lyman, B., Payne, E., &amp; Ashlock, S. (1996, February 17). Writing andaction research. Paper presented at the annual meeting of the Texas AdultLiteracy and Education Conference, San Antonio, TX.<BR><BR>Hoffman, V., &amp; Lyman, B. (1996, February 16). Professionalization ofthe teacher in adult literacy education: Exploring the options. Paper presentedat the annual meeting of the Texas Adult Literacy and Education Conference,San Antonio, TX.<BR><BR>Lyman, B., &amp; others (Payne, E.M., Bader, C., Caverly, D.C., Casazza,M., &amp; Stadulis, J.). (1996, February 4).