<HTML><BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#99CCFF" LINK="#990066" VLINK="#FF0000" ALINK="#339900"><HEAD><TITLE>WEB use in EDA 5348</TITLE><B><H1><CENTER>Using the World Wide Web in EDA 5348</CENTER></H1></B><P><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"><BR><BR>Access to and use of the Internet can provide many opportunities to enhance learning in a course such as EDA 5348.  Since the course meets but once per week but also depends heavily upon interaction among the students and between the students and the professor, the Internet offers a means of accomplishing these learning methods.<P>Each student enrolled in EDA 5348 is expected to:<P><LI>acquire a VAX account from SWT [no charge for enrolled students]<LI>have access to an Internet provider [SWT campus labs, local campus, America OnLine, etc.]<LI>complete class assignments which require Internet access. [The two reflection papers, for example, must be submitted via e-mail to Dr. John Beck at <A HREF="mailto:jb01.swt.edu">jb01.swt.edu</A>]<P><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"><BR>One of the techniques we will use in this course are Chat Rooms and Forums.  To access this service, go to the EDA 5348 <A HREF="http://www.schooledu.swt.edu/interaction">Chat Room and Forum Room</A><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"><BR><CENTER><A HREF="Index.html">Return to EDA 5348 Syllabus Index</A></CENTER></HEAD></BODY></HTML>
