<HTML><BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#99CCFF" LINK="#990066" VLINK="#FF0000" ALINK="#339900"><HEAD><TITLE>EDA 5348 Grading Criteria</TITLE> <!-- Date: Friday, August 23, 1996  12:31 --><P><FONT SIZE=5><B><CENTER>EDA 5348 Syllabus</CENTER></B></FONT><BR><br><br><FONT SIZE=4><P ALIGN = CENTER>Understanding Curriculum andInstructional Leadership</FONT></P><P><FONT SIZE=3><p align=center>Dept. of Educational Administrationand Psychological Services<br>School of Education<BR><A NAME="Top">Southwest Texas State University</A></P></FONT></P><br> </FONT><BR></HEAD><BODY><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><LI><A HREF="#Anchor#1">Grading Criteria</A><LI><A HREF="#Anchor#2">Course Grade Assignment</A><LI><A HREF="#Anchor#3">Reflection Paper Rubric</A><LI><A HREF="#Anchor#4">Content of the Clinical Supervision Report</A><LI><A HREF="#Anchor#5">Content of the Collegial Meeting Report</A><LI><A HREF="#Anchor#6">Grading Rubric for the Group Report</A><BR><LI><A HREF="#Anchor#7">Problem-Based Learning Scoring Rubric</A><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><B><P ALIGN = CENTER><FONT SIZE=4><A NAME="Anchor#1">Grading Criteria</A></FONT></P></B><TABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=2 CELLSPACING=2>  <TR>    <TD>Two reflection papers, each containing 750-1250 words of typed, double-spaced manuscript. Maximum of 20 points per reflection paper</TD>    <TD>40 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>*Clinical supervision cycle</TD>    <TD>30 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Group report on a model of clinical supervision</TD>    <TD>20 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>*Facilitation of a collegial group</TD>    <TD>30 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Promptness, attendance, and participation</TD>    <TD>20 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD><B>MAXIMUM POINTS FOR COURSE</B></TD>    <TD><B>140 POINTS</B></TD>  </TR></TABLE><P><B>*Products of these assignments must be included in the program portfolio.</B><P><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="#top"><---Return to Top of Page---></A></CENTER><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><BR><BR><FONT SIZE=4><B><U><A NAME="Anchor#2"><CENTER>Course Grade Assignment</CENTER></A></U></B></FONT><P><TABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=2 CELLSPACING=2>  <TR>    <TD>A</TD>    <TD>126-140 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>B</TD>    <TD>112-125 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>C</TD>    <TD>98-111 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>D</TD>    <TD>91-97 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>F</TD>    <TD>0-90 points</TD>  </TR></TABLE><P><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="#top"><---Return to Top of Page---></A></CENTER><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><FONT SIZE=4><B><U><A NAME="Anchor#3"><CENTER>Reflection Paper Rubric</CENTER></A></U></B></FONT><BR><TABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=2 CELLSPACING=2>  <TR>    <TD>Includes reference to text reading on selected concept</TD>    <TD>0-4 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Includes reference to class discussion/activities on same concept</TD>    <TD>0-4 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Includes reference to same concept to current work environment</TD>    <TD>0-4 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Includes reference to same concept in future leadership role</TD>    <TD>0-4 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Organization, grammar, style, and length are technically correct</TD>    <TD>0-4 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD><B>MAXIMUM POINTS FOR REFLECTION PAPER</B></TD>    <TD><B>20 POINTS</B></TD>  </TR></TABLE><P><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="#top"><---Return to Top of Page---></A></CENTER><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><FONT SIZE=4><B><U><P ALIGN = CENTER><A NAME="Anchor#4">Content of the Clinical Supervision Report</A></P></U></B></FONT><P>The purpose of this report is to provide an opportunity for you to reflect upon <I>being a supervisor.</I><P><OL><LI>Reflection on the pre-observation conference (teacher's objectives, strategies, concerns, how you went about developing the observation system) [4 points]<LI>Reflection on classroom observation and the data that was collected [4 points]<LI>Reflection on your analysis and planning between the observation and the post-observation conference [3 points]<LI>Reflection on the post-observation conference (supervisory approach used, sharing of data, interpretation of data, discussion of alternatives for future improvement) [4 points]<LI>Reflection on the post-process analysis (feedback you received from the teacher on the value of the first 4 steps and how you can improve your supervisory performance in future clinical supervision cycles) [3 points]<LI>Reflection on a comparison of your actual supervisory behaviors to your supervisory platform [3 points]<LI>Your plan to improve your supervisory behaviors in future clinical supervision of teachers [3 points]<LI>APPENDIX A:  Your supervisory platform [3 points]<LI>APPENDIX B:  Actual data collected during the post-observation conference [3 points]<LI>Submission of an audio [or video] tape of the pre-observation conference, post-observation conference, andpost-process analysis.</OL><B><P ALIGN = CENTER>MAXIMUM POINTS FOR CLINICAL SUPERVISION REPORT: 30</P></B><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="#top"><---Return to Top of Page---></A></CENTER><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><FONT SIZE=4><B><U><P ALIGN = CENTER><A NAME="Anchor#5">Content of the Collegial Meeting Report</A>:  </P></U></B></FONT><P>A.  Planning<OL><LI>Purpose of the meeting (5 points)<LI>Agenda (3 points)<LI>Group norms [how members are expected to behave] (4 points)<LI>Possible discussion questions (4 points)<LI>Participant feedback (3 points)<LI>Plan for continuation [follow-up] (3 points)</OL>B.  Self-evaluation (4 points)<OL><LI>Group roles [how you fostered appropriate task and personal behaviors and dealt with dysfunctional behaviors]<LI>Conflict management<LI>Your overall effectiveness as a group leader</OL>C.  A plan for improving future group leadership (4 points)D.  Audio [or video] tape of the collegial meeting (a requirement, but no points awarded)<B><P ALIGN = CENTER>TOTAL POINTS FOR COLLEGIAL REPORT:  30</P></B><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="#top"><---Return to Top of Page---></A></CENTER><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><FONT SIZE=4><B><U><A NAME="Anchor#6"><CENTER>Grading Rubric for the Group Report</CENTER></A></U></B></FONT><BR><TABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=2 CELLSPACING=2>  <TR>    <TD>Accuracy of description of supervision model [highly accurate and well-described vs. inaccurate and vague]</TD>    <TD>0-10 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Quality of presentation [well-organized  with high involvement by all members vs. disorganized with no evidence of group planning]</TD>    <TD>0-6 points</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Quality and use of visuals [high technical quality and necessary to presentation vs. sloppy visuals with no impact upon presentation</TD>    <TD>0-4 points</TD>  </TR>   <TR>    <TD><B>MAXIMUM POINTS FOR GROUP REPORT</B></TD>    <TD><B>20 POINTS</B></TD>  </TR></TABLE><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="#top"><---Return to Top of Page---></A></CENTER><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><FONT SIZE=5><B><U><P ALIGN = CENTER><A NAME="Anchor#7">Problem-Based Learning Scoring Rubric</A></P></U></B></FONT><P><B><FONT SIZE=4>Definition</FONT></B><BR><P>Problem-Based Learning [PBL] is a method of instruction which simulates real-world practice.  The PBL activity is grounded in theory but enables students to gain insight into real-world of practice.<P><B><FONT SIZE=4>Peer Assessment Sheet/Problem-Based Learning</FONT></B><BR><P>Topic: _______________________________________________________<P><B><FONT SIZE=4>Directions</FONT></B><BR><P>Analyze the product(s), the presentation, and the discussion for the presenting group by applying the criteria below and circling the appropriate number.  Your assessment must be supported by evidence that is observed or found in the product, presentation, or discussion.<P><B>Did the group successfully fulfill the learning objectives outlined in the problem?<P></B><TABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=4 CELLPADDING=4 CELLSPACING=4>  <TR>    <TD>10</TD>    <TD>9</TD>    <TD>8</TD>    <TD>7</TD>    <TD>6</TD>    <TD>5</TD>    <TD>4</TD>  </TR></TABLE><P><UL><LI>10: 	The group clearly and completely fulfilled the learning objectives outlined in the problem.  The solutions were presented in detail and reflected an unusually thorough understanding of and concern for the implications of the decision.<BR><LI>8-9:	The group clearly fulfilled the learning objectives.  With no significant exceptions, the solutions were appropriate for the facts of the problem.<BR><LI>6-7:	The group adequately fulfilled the learning objectives.  Some solutions and/or some important factors relevant to the problem may have been omitted.<BR><LI>4-5:	The group did not fulfill the learning objectives and/or the specified solutions were not appropriate for the facts of the problem.</UL><B>Did the group apply accurate and important research information to the decision-making process for this problem?</B><P><TABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=4 CELLPADDING=4 CELLSPACING=4>  <TR>    <TD>10</TD>    <TD>9</TD>    <TD>8</TD>    <TD>7</TD>    <TD>6</TD>    <TD>5</TD>    <TD>4</TD>  </TR></TABLE><P><UL><LI>10: 	The group accurately and thoroughly applied research information to the decision-making process for this problem.  The information was presented in detail and reflected an unusually thorough understanding of the decision-making process as it related to this problem.<BR><LI>8-9:	The group clearly applied research information to the decision-making process for this problem.  The information used was appropriate for the facts of the problem<BR><LI>6-7:	The group adequately applied research information to the decsion-making process for this problem.  Some cirtical steps may have been omitted or some steps were included which were not relevant to the problem.<BR><LI>4-5:	The group did not apply a deicsion making process to the problem or an incorrect process was applied or an inaccurate process was applied.</UL><B>Did the group's recommended decision match the learning objectives for the problem?</B><P><TABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=4 CELLPADDING=4 CELLSPACING=4>  <TR>    <TD>10</TD>    <TD>9</TD>    <TD>8</TD>    <TD>7</TD>    <TD>6</TD>    <TD>5</TD>    <TD>4</TD>  </TR></TABLE><P><UL><LI>10: 	The group's final decision clearly and completely matched the learning objectives outlined in the problem.  The decision was presented in detail and reflected an unusually thorough understanding of and concern for problem resolution.<BR><LI>8-9:	The group's final decision clearly matched the learning objectives.  With no significant exceptions, the decision was appropriate and provided a realistic resollution of the problem.<BR><LI>6-7:	The group's final decision adequately matched the learning objectives.  Some elements of the recommended decision were missing or lacked clarity.<BR><LI>4-5:	The group's final decision did not match the learning objectives with an appropriate solution.</UL><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="#top"><---Return to Top of Page---></A></CENTER><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><P ALIGN = CENTER><B><A HREF="Index.html">Return to EDA 5348 Syllabus Index</A><U></U></B></P><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER></BODY><BR><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="spunwithps.gif" WIDTH="88" HEIGHT="31"></CENTER></HTML>
