<HTML><BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#99CCFF" LINK="#990066" VLINK="#FF0000" ALINK="#339900"><HEAD><TITLE>EDA 5348 Student Portfolios</TITLE> <!-- Date: Friday, August 23, 1996  12:31 --><CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>EDA 5348 Syllabus</B></FONT><P><FONT SIZE=4>Understanding Curriculum andInstructional Leadership</FONT><BR><FONT SIZE=3>Dept. of Educational Administrationand Psychological Services<br>School of Education<BR>Southwest Texas State University</P></FONT></FONT></HEAD><BODY><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"><FONT SIZE=5><B><U>Student Portfolios</P></U></B></FONT></CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=4>Definition</FONT></B><BR><P>The student's portfolio is a collection of materials submitted by the student which represent the student's cumulative learning activities in the core courses of the Educational Administration Program.  All students are required to place certain assignments in their portfolio, and they are free to submit optional materials for evaluation.  These optional materials may include, but are not limited to formal presentations developed by the student, results of literature searches, personal journals, etc.<P><P><B><FONT SIZE=4>Purpose</FONT></B><BR><P>The purposes of the portfolio are to document the student's data collection and clinical reasoning process; to provide practice in essential written communication skills; to facilitate the student's self-directed learning by formalizing the process of identification and discussion of learning issues; and to provide a measure of student competence for assessment by program faculty.<P><P><B><FONT SIZE=4>Criteria</FONT></B><BR><P>Required portfolio submissions are evaluated according to the rubrics associated with the assignment.  The optional materials are evaluated by using a single  criterion:  the degree to which the materials meet one or more of the purposes for portfolio development.<P><P><B><FONT SIZE=4>Feedback and Remediation</FONT></B><BR><P>Professors in each of the five core courses will provide written and oral feedback to the student regarding portfolio development.  This feedback will occur at a time agreed upon by the professor and the student.  Even though no grade will accrue to the portfolio, students are expected to revise portfolio content as agreed upon between the professor and the student.<CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"><A HREF="#top"><---Return to Top of Page---></A><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"><B><A HREF="Index.html">Return to EDA 5348 Syllabus Index</A></B></P></BODY><CENTER><IMG SRC="spunwithps.gif" WIDTH="88" HEIGHT="31"></CENTER></HTML>
