<HTML><BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#99CCFF" LINK="#990066" VLINK="#FF0000" ALINK="#339900"><HEAD><TITLE>EDA 5348 Action Research</TITLE> <!-- Date: Friday, August 23, 1996  12:31 --><P><FONT SIZE=5><B><CENTER>EDA 5348 Syllabus</CENTER></B></FONT><BR><br><br><FONT SIZE=4><P ALIGN = CENTER>Understanding Curriculum andInstructional Leadership</FONT></P><P><FONT SIZE=3><p align=center>Dept. of Educational Administrationand Psychological Services<br>School of Education<BR>Southwest Texas State University<BR></P></FONT></P><br> </FONT><BR></HEAD><BODY><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=4><P ALIGN = CENTER>Action Research</P></FONT></B><P ALIGN = CENTER>from</P><BR><P ALIGN = CENTER>Glickman, C.D., Gordon, S. P., and Ross-Gordon, J. M. (1995).  <I>Supervision of Instruction:  A Developmental Approach</I>.  Allyn &amp; Bacon</P><BR><BR><B><FONT SIZE=4>The Concept</FONT></B><BR><BR>Our operational definition of action research will be that expressed by the authors: <BR><I> ". . . action research in education is study conducted by colleagues in a school setting of the results of their activities to improve intruction."</I><BR><BR><B><FONT SIZE=3>Key characteristics</FONT></B><BR><BR><UL><LI>best done as cooperative endeavor<LI>goal is to improve on a common instructional concern<LI>practitioners are the researchers<LI>benefits to practice outweigh loss of experimental purity</UL><P><B><FONT SIZE=4>Steps in Action Research</FONT></B><BR><BR><B><U><FONT SIZE=3>problem-identification</FONT></U></B><UL><LI>identify a schoolwide area of interest focused on teaching and learning</UL><B><U><FONT SIZE=3>planning phase</FONT></U></B><BR><UL><LI>decide what data will be collected<LI>how it will be collected<LI>how often it will be collected<LI>what resources are needed to collect it</UL><B><U><FONT SIZE=3>organization phase</FONT></U></B><BR><UL><LI>how data can best be organized<LI>how data can best be presented</UL><B><U><FONT SIZE=3>evaluation phase</FONT></U></B><BR><UL><LI>analyze data<LI>interpret data in light of stated goals and objectives</UL><B><U><FONT SIZE=3>action phase</FONT></U></B><BR><UL><LI>revise and modify goals, objectives, and activities based upon the analysis and interpretation of results</UL><BR><P><B><FONT SIZE=4>Decisions about action research</FONT></B><BR><BR><OL><LI>First, the team conducts a needs assessment of faculty to determine common goals for improvement of instruction<LI>Second, the team brainstorms activities that  will cut across supervision tasks<LI>Third, the team makes a plan relating activities to goals<LI>Fourth, the team determines ways to observe the progress of the action plan as it is implemented in classrooms<LI>Fifth, the team chooses an effective research and evaluation design.</OL><BR><P><B><FONT SIZE=4>Rubric for Assessing the Quality of an Action Research Project</FONT></B><BR><TABLE WIDTH=100% BORDER=4 CELLPADDING=2 CELLSPACING=2>  <TR>    <TD>Intent to improve upon a common instructional concern is evident [0-5 points: no attempt to determine common concerns to quality needs assessment and brainstorming]</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Steps to effective action research are followed [0-10 points: no evidence of a systematic approach to clear delineation and integration of the 5 steps]</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Design for research and evaluation is effective [0-5 points: no justification for the design to a design which enables team to analyze data, determine whether objectives have been met, and decide what further actions are necessary]</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Action research report is clear and concise [0-5 points: disorganized, confusing, and thoughtless to easy-to-follow attention to each step in the process]</TD>  </TR>  <TR>    <TD>Critique is reflective and informative [0-5 points: no critique supplied to effective reflection upon the action research process, its accrued benefits, and consideration of activities that  might be changed in the next application of action research]</TD>  </TR></TABLE><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER><P ALIGN = CENTER><B><A HREF="Index.html">Return to EDA 5348 Syllabus Index</A><U></U></B></P><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="faucetline.gif" WIDTH="582" HEIGHT="23"></CENTER></BODY><CENTER><IMG ALIGN=Absmiddle SRC="spunwithps.gif" WIDTH="88" HEIGHT="31"></CENTER></HTML>
