<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>Sprouting Out</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#f8fcc5"><H2></H2><H2><CENTER>Sprouting Out:<IMG SRC="Images/image2.gif" WIDTH="144" HEIGHT="111" ALIGN=bottom NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></CENTER></H2><H2>Our Growth Through the Year</H2><BR><B>Amy</B>: &quot;I have been hit with the reality of teaching in the publicschools. TAAS, politics, red-tape, developmentally inappropriate curriculumhave made me sadder, but wiser. I still hold strong beliefs about the waychildren learn and the way teachers should teach, but I wrestle daily withthe reality of the situation I find myself in. When I began this program,I honestly believed I could do it all. Now I don't worry so much about doingit all. I do my best and pray for the rest.<BR><BR><B>Josie</B>: &quot;My views of the teaching profession were pretty vague.I knew what I wanted to do and how I wanted my classroom to be, but it wasn'tuntil I learned how to put the pieces together that I realized how my viewshave changed.&quot; <BR><BR><B>Lisa</B>: &quot;My views on research and teaching have changed. I neverpictured myself relating recent research to my class. I thought I wouldgo in, receive a curriculum guide, teach, and be done. Now I see that keepingabreast on research is very beneficial.&quot;<BR><BR><B>Margaret</B>: &quot;A year ago I believed that a teacher's responsibilityended at the door of her classroom. I know now I have a responsibility toevery student - even after I have gone home. We can only do this throughour own evaluation as teachers and commitment to our students well-being.&quot;<H4><CENTER><A HREF="FellowsHome">Home</A><A HREF="fellows%20home"> </A>/<A HREF="Gardens">Garden</A> / <A HREF="sprouting">Sprout</A> / <A HREF="grape">Grapevine</A>/ <A HREF="Sunnydays">Sunshine</A></CENTER></H4></BODY></HTML>
