<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>grapevine</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#bcfccc"><H2></H2><H2><CENTER>News Through the Grapevine<IMG SRC="Images/image5.gif" WIDTH="144" HEIGHT="135" ALIGN=middle NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></CENTER></H2><H2>Teacher Fellows' Reflections </H2><B>Why I chose to become a teacher fellow:</B> <BR><BR><B>Karen</B>: &quot;I was very interested in continuing my education andwanted the support and collaboration that this program offers.&quot; <BR><B>Lesli</B>: &quot;To take advantage of an opportunity to share ideas andconcerns with other first year teachers, and to continue my education whileincorporating current ideas into my teaching.&quot; <BR><BR><BR><B>My exchange teacher helps me by: <BR><BR>Sylvia</B>: &quot;coordinating study groups for our graduate courses andsupplying us with supplemental teaching materials appropriate to our gradelevel. She offers both emotional support a long with her experienced mannerof dealing with everyday procedures.&quot; <BR><B>Jennifer</B>: &quot;providing resources, reassurance, sympathy, and lunch!&quot;<BR><BR><BR><B>What I liked best about being a Teacher Fellow is:<BR><BR>Teresa</B>: &quot;the camaraderie that we have among the Fellows. We reallywork well together and we watch out for each other.&quot; <BR><B>Farah</B>: &quot;the support created by the exchange teacher and fromthe other Teacher Fellows. There are times I would have screamed withoutthe support.&quot; <BR><BR><BR><B>What I like best about engaging in graduate study is: <BR><BR>David</B>: &quot;I am exposed to ideas and philosophies that are being usedsuccessfully in schools around the country.&quot; <BR><B>Ashley</B>: &quot;learning, learning, learning!! I've learned more thisyear than I could ever have imagined.&quot; <H4><CENTER><A HREF="FellowsHome">Home</A><A HREF="fellows%20home"> </A>/<A HREF="Gardens">Garden</A> / <A HREF="sprouting">Sprout</A> / <A HREF="grape">Grapevine</A>/ <A HREF="Sunnydays">Sunshine</A></CENTER></H4></BODY></HTML>
