<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>On-Line.Experts</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BACKGROUND="blumarbl.gif"><H1><IMG SRC="NADEspinlogo.GIF" WIDTH="72" HEIGHT="84" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3">NADE - Technology SPIN</H1><H5><A HREF="NADE_Technology_SPIN">(return back to NADE Technology SPINhomepage)</A></H5><H1><CENTER><HR><A NAME="anchor190944"></A>Overview</CENTER></H1><DL>  <DT>Below is a <A HREF="#anchor166490">list</A> of members of the NationalAssociation of Developmental Educators (NADE) Technology Special Interest(SPIN) group. Members are listed alphabetically with a link to those memberswilling to answer questions via e-mail. <BR><BR>In addition, many members have agreed to serve as <A HREF="#anchor309651">on-lineexperts</A> by answering questions regarding <A HREF="#anchor175182">hardware</A>(for Macintosh and PC or compatible) as well as for <A HREF="#anchor175307">software</A>.We have broken software into its use as a <I><A HREF="#anchor148115">tutor</A></I>(where the computer is attempting to teach specific skills to its user via<A HREF="#anchor148591">drill and practice</A>, <A HREF="#anchor148760">tutorials</A>,or <A HREF="#anchor149151">simulations</A>), as a <I><A HREF="#anchor149306">tool</A></I>(where the user is creating a variety of products via <A HREF="#anchor149463">wordprocessing</A>, <A HREF="#anchor149651">databases</A>, <A HREF="#anchor149814">spreadsheets</A>,<A HREF="#anchor149975">graphics</A>, <A HREF="#anchor150145">desktop publishing</A>,<A HREF="#anchor150300">presentation packages</A>, <A HREF="#anchor150472">utilities</A>,and <A HREF="#anchor156973">management</A>), and as a <I><A HREF="#anchor158192">tutee</A></I>(where the user is asking the computer to do his/her bidding via the productionof <A HREF="#anchor158332">hypermedia</A> and through <A HREF="#anchor158457">telecommunications</A>).</DL><H2><IMG SRC="../Gifs/bluexedbar.gif" WIDTH="595" HEIGHT="5" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></H2><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor166490"></A>1996-1997<BR>Membership List</CENTER></H2><H4><A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly, Co-Chair</A><BR><BR><A HREF="mailto:CP06@SWT.edu">Dr. Cynthia Peterson, Co-Chair</A></H4><H5><A HREF="#anchor190944"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/return.back.button.GIF" WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> back to overview</A></H5><P><CENTER><IMG SRC="../Gifs/bluexedbar.gif" WIDTH="595" HEIGHT="9" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> </CENTER><H1><CENTER><A NAME="anchor309651"></A>On-Line Expertise</CENTER></H1><H2><CENTER><IMG SRC="../Gifs/bluexedbar.gif" WIDTH="595" HEIGHT="8" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR><A NAME="anchor175182"></A>Hardware<BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="589" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR></CENTER></H2><H3>Macintosh: </H3><DL>  <DD><A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly</A>   <DT><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"> </DL><H3>IBM - PC or compatible </H3><DL>  <DD>Dr. Bill Broderick </DL><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H2>UNIX </H2><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H2>audio </H2><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H2>video </H2><H5><A HREF="#anchor190944"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/return.back.button.GIF" WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> back to overview</A></H5><P><CENTER><IMG SRC="../Gifs/bluexedbar.gif" WIDTH="595" HEIGHT="8" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> </CENTER><H1><CENTER><A NAME="anchor175307"></A>Software:Computer as Tutor</CENTER></H1><P><CENTER><IMG SRC="../Gifs/bluexedbar.gif" WIDTH="595" HEIGHT="8" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor148591"></A>Drill and Practice <BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3>Spell-It<BR></H3><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H3>Speed Reading</H3><DL>  <DT><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></DL><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor148760"></A>Tutorials<BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><I>Using your Biology Textbook Effectively</I></H3><H4>An effective tutorial for teaching students how to read and study sciencetextbooks, particularly biology. Covers notetaking, mapping, and review.<A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly</A></H4><H5><A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu"></A></H5><H5><CENTER><A HREF="#anchor190944"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/return.back.button.GIF"WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> back to overview</A><BR><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H3><I>Using your Psychology Textbook Effectively</I></H3><H4>An effective tutorial for teaching students how to read and study socialscience textbooks, particularly psychology texts.. Covers notetaking, mapping,and review. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly</A></H4><DL>  <DT><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"> </CENTER></DL><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor149151"></A>Simulations <BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><I>EndNote Plus</I></H3><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H3><I>Inspiration<BR></I></H3><P><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER><H3><I>More</I></H3><H4>A wonderful outlining program that simulates the creation of semanticmaps and slide shows. We use it to teach students the difference betweenmain ideas and details as well as text structure. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr.David Caverly</A></H4><H5><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></H5><H3><I>Writer's Helper</I></H3><H4>A simulation tutorial taking students through process writing. Exceptionalbrainstorming and editing tools, <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. DavidCaverly</A></H4><H5><A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu"></A></H5><H5><CENTER><A HREF="#anchor190944"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/return.back.button.GIF"WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> back to overview</A></CENTER></H5><IMG SRC="../Gifs/bluexedbar.gif" WIDTH="595" HEIGHT="8" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"><H1><CENTER><A NAME="anchor149306"></A>Computer as Tool</CENTER></H1><P><CENTER><IMG SRC="../Gifs/bluexedbar.gif" WIDTH="595" HEIGHT="8" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor149463"></A>word processing <BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><I>Microsoft Word</I></H3><H4>Powerful word processor. Latest version (6.0) includes a wonderful revisiontool marking changes made during a collaborative editing process. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr.David Caverly</A></H4><H5><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H3><I>ClarisWorks</I></H3><H4>Semi-powerful integrated word processor, database, spreadsheet, graphics,and communication programs. Probably the most used program in public schools.<A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly</A></H4><H5><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H3><I>WordPerfect</I></H3><P><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor149651"></A>databases <BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><I>ClarisWorks</I></H3><H4>Semi-powerful integrated word processor, database, spreadsheet, graphics,and communication programs. Probably the most used program in public schools.<A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly.</A></H4><H5><CENTER><A HREF="#anchor190944"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/return.back.button.GIF"WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> back to overview</A><HR></CENTER></H5><H3><I>FileMaker Pro</I></H3><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H3><I>FoxPro</I></H3><H5><CENTER> <HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor149814"></A>spreadsheets <BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><I>ClarisWorks</I></H3><H4>Semi-powerful integrated word processor, database, spreadsheet, graphics,and communication programs. Probably the most used program in public schools.<A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly.</A></H4><H5><A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu"></A></H5><H5><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor149975"></A>graphics programs<BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><I>ClarisWorks</I></H3><H4>Semi-powerful integrated word processor, database, spreadsheet, graphics,and communication programs. Probably the most used program in public schools.<A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly.</A></H4><H5><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H3><I>Canvas</I></H3><H5><CENTER><A HREF="#anchor190944"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/return.back.button.GIF"WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> back to overview<BR></A><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H4></H4><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor150145"></A>desktop publishing<BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><I>ClarisWorks</I></H3><H4>Semi-powerful integrated word processor, database, spreadsheet, graphics,and communication programs. Probably the most used program in public schools.<A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly.</A></H4><H5><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H3><I>PageMaker</I></H3><H4><A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu"></A></H4><H4><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H4><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor150300"></A>presentation packages<BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><I>More</I></H3><H4>An outling program that simulates the creation of semantic maps andslide shows. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly</A></H4><H4><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H4><H3><I>PowerPoint<BR></I></H3><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H3><I>Persuasion</I></H3><H5><CENTER><A HREF="#anchor190944"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/return.back.button.GIF"WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> back to overview</A></CENTER></H5><H5></H5><H5><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor150472"></A>utilities <BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><CENTER>screen savers</CENTER></H3><H3><I>AfterDark</I></H3><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5">disk recovery programs </CENTER></H3><H3><I>Norton Utilities</I></H3><H4>Collection of programs that allow you to recover a crashed hard or floppydisk, fix damaged disks, backup, optomize your disk, etc. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr.David Caverly</A><BR><BR></H4><H3><I>MacTools</I></H3><H4><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H4><H3><CENTER>anti-virus programs</CENTER></H3><H3><I>Symantec Anti-virus for Mac (SAM)</I> </H3><H4>Powerful virus protection program also allowing us to disable our floppydisk drives so students cannot insert disk with viruses. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr.David Caverly.</A></H4><H5><A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu"></A></H5><H5><CENTER><A HREF="#anchor190944"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/return.back.button.GIF"WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> back to overview</A><BR><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H3><CENTER>disk compression programs</CENTER></H3><H4><I>Stuffit Deluxe</I><BR>Compression program that allows you to reduce the size of a file to storemore on floppy or hard disks. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly.</A></H4><H5><A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu"><BR></A><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></H5><H4><I>Zip and DeZip</I></H4><H5><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"><BR></CENTER></H5><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor156973"></A>management<BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><I>FileMaker Pro</I></H3><H4>Powerful database program allowing for multiple users in one databaseas well as WWW accessible databases. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. DavidCaverly</A></H4><H5><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H3><BR><I>FoxPro</I></H3><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H3><I>Excel</I></H3><H5><CENTER><A HREF="#anchor190944"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/return.back.button.GIF"WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> back to overview</A></CENTER></H5><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H4><I>SPSS</I><BR>Benchmark program for doing serious statistical analysis of research andevaluation efforts. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly</A></H4><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H3>StatView</H3><H4>Powerful, yet accessible statistical analysis program with useful graphicalpresentations. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. Cynthia Peterson</A></H4><H5><A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu"></A></H5><H5><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H2><CENTER>diagnostic<BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H2></H2><H3>E-Lassi<BR></H3><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H3>Guides<BR></H3><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H3>Accuplacer</H3><H1><CENTER><IMG SRC="../Gifs/bluexedbar.gif" WIDTH="595" HEIGHT="9" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> <A NAME="anchor158192"></A>Computer as Tutee<BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/bluexedbar.gif" WIDTH="595" HEIGHT="9" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H1><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor158332"></A>hypermedia <BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><I>HyperStudio</I></H3><H4>Authoring program for creating hypermedia software with color, animation,audio, and video. Latest version (3.0) allows for connection to the WWW.Major program used in public schools for the creation of hypermedia. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr.David Caverly.</A></H4><H5><A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu"></A></H5><H5><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H3><I>HyperCard</I></H3><H4>Older program to create hypermedia. Latest version (2.3.1) allows forcolor. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly</A></H4><P><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER><H2><CENTER><A NAME="anchor158457"></A>telecommunications<BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/eyeslineleft.gif" WIDTH="586" HEIGHT="13" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H2><H3><CENTER>e-mail</CENTER></H3><H4><I>Telnet</I><BR>Public domain communication program for connecting to the Internet whenhardwired. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr. David Caverly</A></H4><H5><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></H5><H3>Gopher, Archie, Veronica,Lynx</H3><H4>Tools for those without WWW access to search the Internet. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr.David Caverly</A></H4><H5><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H5><H2><CENTER>World Wide Web</CENTER></H2><H3><I>Netscape Navigator</I></H3><H5>First, and still one of the more effective WWW browsers. Latest version(3.0) allows you to create web pages within your browswer. <A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu">Dr.David Caverly</A></H5><H3><CENTER><HR WIDTH="99%" SIZE="5"></CENTER></H3><H3><I>Internet Explorer</I></H3><H5><CENTER><A HREF="#anchor190944"><IMG SRC="../Gifs/return.back.button.GIF"WIDTH="23" HEIGHT="18" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> back to overview</A><BR><IMG SRC="../Gifs/bluexedbar.gif" WIDTH="595" HEIGHT="9" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER></H5><H5><A HREF="NADE_Technology_SPIN"><IMG SRC="NADEspinlogo.GIF" WIDTH="36"HEIGHT="38" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="BOTTOM">return to NADE TechnologySPIN homepage</A> </H5><H3><CENTER><BR><HR></CENTER></H3><H2><CENTER>Send comments to Webmaster: <BR><A HREF="mailto:DC02@SWT.edu"><IMG SRC="mail.gif" WIDTH="40" HEIGHT="40"ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></A></CENTER></H2><P><CENTER><B><I>Webmaster: David C. Caverly, Ph.D.; <BR>DC&Oslash;2@SWT.edu <BR>November, 1996</I></B></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
