<HEAD>

<TITLE>MEMBERSHIP BENEFITS/SERVICES</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="../pics/PARCH.GIF">

<HR>
<P>
<CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=6>MEMBERSHIP BENEFITS/SERVICES</FONT></B></CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<B>
The Membership Department coordinates the production and distribution
of an annual pictorial membership roster.  A Special feature of
the Roster is a breakdown by Specialty by County of the membership.
 The roster is available in July to each member.  Additional copies
for home or office may be purchased.  Also included in the Roster
is a listing with home addresses of the Members of the Alliance
to MASA.<BR>
<BR>
Other regular publications are:  The Alabama M.D. - MASA's weekly
newsletter, with an emphasis on medical socio-economic issues
impacting medicine in Alabama and the nation; Alabama Medicine
- the quarterly medical science and technology magazine of the
Association.<BR>
<BR>
Currently there are 5,700 MASA members.<BR>
<BR>
Send us the name of a colleague you recommend for membership --
Fax (334) 269-5200 or 1-800-239-6272 or write to MASA membership
Department, P. O. Box 1900, Montgomery, Alabama 36102-1900, or
if you have any questions about the Medical Association of the
State of Alabama or its services.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=4>MEMBERSHIP BENEFITS<BR>
ARCHIVAL<BR>
<BR>
</FONT></CENTER>
<P>
Contact the MASA Membership Department for information on the
MASA sponsored Blue Cross Blue Shield group health insurance plans
for you and your staff:  Telephone 1-800-239-6272, (334) 263-6441;
Fax (334) 269-5200.<BR>
<BR>
Information on other types of insurance including professional
liability, life, disability, business overhead to name a few is
available by contacting Mutual Assurance Agency, P. O. Box 590009,
Birmingham, Alabama 35259; telephone 1-800-282-6242.<BR>
<BR>
Other member-benefit service programs offered include:<BR>
<BR>
</B>

<P>
