<CENTER><H1>LEGAL GUIDE<BR>
FOR<BR>
PHYSICIANS IN ALABAMA<P></H1>
<H4>Original authors:<BR>
John T. Mooresmith<BR>
Howard E. Bogard<BR>
and<BR>
Heather C. Harrison</H4><P>

<H2>BURR & FORMAN</H2>
<H4>Birmingham, Alabama</H4>
<H5>Compiled January 1996</H5></CENTER><HR>
<CENTER><H3><A NAME="TOC">Table of Contents</A></H3>
<H4>|<A HREF=#A> A </A>|<A HREF=#B> B </A>|<A HREF=#C> C </A>|<A HREF=#D> D </A>|<A HREF=#E> E </A>|<A HREF=#F> F </A>|<A HREF=#G> G </A>|<A HREF=#H> H </A>|<A HREF=#I> I </A>|<A HREF=#J> J </A>|<A HREF=#J> K </A>|<A HREF=#J> L </A>|<A HREF=#M> M </A>|<A HREF=#N> N </A>|<A HREF=#O> O </A>|<A HREF=#P> P </A>|<A HREF=#R> Q </A>|<A HREF=#R> R </A>|<A HREF=#S> S </A>|<A HREF=#T> T </A>|<A HREF=#T> U </A>|<A HREF=#V> V </A>|<A HREF=#V> W </A>|<A HREF=#V> X </A>|<A HREF=#V> Y </A>|<A HREF=#V> Z </A>|<A HREF="#APPY"> Appendix </A>|</H4></CENTER><P>
<B><A NAME="A"><A HREF="LEGMEDA.HTM#ABO">ABORTION</A></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>May a minor consent to an abortion?<BR>
What are the penalties for performing an abortion on a
 minor without proper consent?<BR>
What information can be disclosed by a physician?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDA.HTM#ABU">ABUSE REPORTING</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What are a physician's responsibilities in reporting suspected abuse?<BR>
Does the physician/patient relationship bar a physician from reporting<BR>
evidence of suspected abuse?</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>

<A HREF="LEGMEDA.HTM#ADVD">ADVANCED DECLARATION</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is an advanced declaration?<BR>
What is a terminal condition?<BR>
What are the specific requirements for a valid advanced declaration under Alabama law?<BR>
Who may not be a witness to an advanced declaration?<BR>
How is a physician notified of the existence of an advanced declaration?<BR>
May a physician lawfully refuse to comply with an advanced declaration?<BR>
Is a person required to complete an advanced declaration?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDA.HTM#ADV">ADVERTISING</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What advertisements are prohibited by the Alabama Board of Medical Examiners?<BR>
What are the penalties for a prohibited advertisement?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDA.HTM#ADA">AMERICANS WITH DISABILITIES ACT ("ADA")</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is the ADA?<BR>
What does the ADA require?<BR>
How does the ADA address architectural barriers?<BR>
How does the ADA affect physician practices?<BR>
What are the employment implications under the ADA?<BR>
Who enforces the ADA and what are the potential penalties?<BR>
What should a physician do to avoid unlawful discrimination<BR>
against individuals with disabilities?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDA.HTM#AKS">ANTI-KICKBACK STATUTE</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is the "anti-kickback" statute?<BR>
Who enforces the anti-kickback statute?<BR>
What happens if a physician is found to be in violation of
the anti-kickback statute?<BR>
Are there any exceptions to the anti-kickback statute?<BR>
Do the enforcement agencies focus on any particular areas?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDA.HTM#ANTST">ANTITRUST</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What are the antitrust laws?<BR>
What type of conduct generally violates the antitrust laws?<BR>
May a large physician group be considered a monopoly?<BR>
Are there any antitrust guidelines which address managed care organizations?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDA.HTM#ASP">ASSET PROTECTION</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>In Alabama, what assets are protected from creditors?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDA.HTM#APA">ASSISTANT TO PHYSICIANS</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Who is an Assistant to a Physician?<BR>
What services may be performed by an Assistant to a Physician?<BR>
May an Assistant to a Physician prescribe drugs?<BR>
May an Assistant to a Physician practice at remote sites?<BR>
Where can physicians obtain additional information about Assistants to Physicians?</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A NAME="B"><A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#BIL">BILLING</A></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>May a physician charge a late fee or interest on an unpaid balance?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#BIR">BIRTH AND DEATH CERTIFICATES</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>May a physician obtain a copy of a birth or death certificate?<BR>
When must a birth certificate be filed?</BLOCKQUOTE>
<A NAME="C"><A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#CAN">CANCER REPORTING</A></A><P>

<A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#CLI">CLINICS WITHOUT WALLS</A><P>

<A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#CONF">CONFIDENTIALITY OF MEDICAL INFORMATION</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What sources of law affect medical records?<BR>
Who owns the medical record?<BR>
Does Alabama law treat medical records as privileged from disclosure?<BR>
When does a physician have an obligation to disclose information contained in a medical record?<BR>
Can a patient waive his or her right to confidentiality?<BR>
When medical records are requested, who pays the copy costs?<BR>
How much can be charged for copying medical records?<BR>
What is a physician's duty to hold patient information in confidence?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#CONS">CONSENT TO TREATMENT</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>When is consent not required?<BR>
When is consent of a missing husband or wife not required?<BR>
When may a physician treat a minor without parental consent?<BR>
Will a physician incur liability for accepting the consent of a minor?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#CME">CONTINUING MEDICAL EDUCATION ("CME")</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What are the CME requirements in Alabama?<BR>
What are the CME requirements for initial licensure?<BR>
What are the CME requirements for retired physicians?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#CTR">CONTRACTING ISSUES</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is a valid contract?<BR>
What is generally required to form a valid contract in Alabama?<BR>
What is a non-competition clause?<BR>
Are non-competition clauses enforceable against physicians?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#CSUB">CONTROLLED SUBSTANCES REGISTRATION</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What are the general requirements for dispensing controlled substances?<BR>
What constitutes grounds for suspension or revocation of a physician's Controlled Substances Registration Certificate?<BR>
What rules apply to the prescribing of Schedule II controlled substances?<BR>
What occurs upon the suspension or revocation of a physician's
Controlled Substances Registration Certificate?<BR>
May the State Board of Medical Examiners suspend a physician's
Controlled Substances Registration Certificate without prior notice?<BR>
What fines may be imposed upon a physician for violating the
Controlled Substances Statute?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A NAME="D"><A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#DEA">DEATH CERTIFICATES</A></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>When must a death certificate be filed?<BR>
When must a fetal death certificate be filed?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#DEP">DEPOSITIONS</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is a deposition?<BR>
What happens when you are asked to give a deposition?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#DRI">DRIVERS LICENSE ADVISORY BOARD</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is the Drivers License Advisory Board?<BR>
Is there immunity associated with making a report to the Drivers
License Advisory Board?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A NAME="E"><A HREF="LEGMEDBE.HTM#EMP">EMPLOYEE/INDEPENDENT CONTRACTOR</A></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is the difference between an employee and an independent contractor?<BR>
What are the tax consequences of improperly characterizing an
individual as either an employee or independent contractor?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A NAME="F"><A HREF="LEGMEDFM.HTM#FEE">FEES AND FEE SPLITTING</A></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is the general rule regarding physician's fees?<BR>
May a physician charge different fees for the same service?<BR>
May a physician split his or her fees received for professional
services with a referring party?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDFM.HTM#FOR">FORCE, USE OF</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>When is a physician authorized to use force?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A NAME="G"><A HREF="LEGMEDFM.HTM#GOO">GOOD SAMARITAN LAW</A></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is the good samaritan law?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A NAME="H"><A HREF="LEGMEDFM.HTM#HIV">HIV TESTING</A></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What are the general requirements for HIV testing?<BR>
What is a physician's duty upon diagnosis of HIV infection?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A NAME="I"><A HREF="LEGMEDFM.HTM#IMP">IMPAIRED PHYSICIANS</A></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is the Impaired Physicians Committee?<BR>
Does the Impaired Physicians Committee notify the Board
of Medical Examiners of its evaluation?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A NAME="J"><A HREF="LEGMEDFM.HTM#JUR">JURY DUTY</A></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>May a physician be excused from jury duty?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A NAME="M"><A HREF="LEGMEDFM.HTM#MLIC">MEDICAL LICENSURE</A></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What are the general requirements for a certificate of qualification
to practice medicine in Alabama?<BR>
What are the post-graduate requirements?<BR>
What are the examination requirements?<BR>
What are the requirements for foreign medical graduates?<BR>
Are there additional requirements for certain applicants?<BR>
Is there an interview requirement?<BR>
What is the fee for filing an application?<BR>
What is the Board of Medical Examiners' policy regarding applicants who have
been treated for chemical dependency, substance abuse or mental illness?<BR>
What constitutes grounds for denial of a certificate of qualification?<BR>
What acts or offenses constitute sufficient grounds for the suspension
or revocation of a physician's license?<BR>
What is unprofessional conduct?<BR>
May a physician be fined for violating the Medical Licensure
Commission regulations?<BR>
What are the penalties for submitting a fraudulent application?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDFM.HTM#MMAL">MEDICAL MALPRACTICE</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is the degree of care owed to a patient?<BR>
For insurance companies, what are the medical malpractice
reporting requirements?<BR>
For physicians, what are the medical malpractice reporting requirements?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDFM.HTM#MWA">MEDICAL WASTES</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What are medical wastes?<BR>
What is the proper method of disposing of medical wastes?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A NAME="N"><A HREF="LEGMEDNP.HTM#NDAT">NATIONAL PRACTITIONER DATA BANK ("DATA BANK")</A></A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>What is the Data Bank?<BR>
What entities are covered under the Data Bank's reporting
and inquiry requirements?<BR>
What types of malpractice payments must be reported?<BR>
What types of actions must be reported by state medical boards?<BR>
What types of actions must be reported by a hospital?<BR>
When must a hospital request information from the Data Bank?<BR>
What types of actions must be reported by professional societies?<BR>
May a plaintiff's attorney request information from the Data Bank?<BR>
Can a physician challenge a Data Bank report?<BR>
If a report is made to the Data Bank, does a physician have a means
of "explaining" the report?</BLOCKQUOTE>

<A HREF="LEGMEDNP.HTM#NOT">NOTIFIABLE DISEASES</A>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Does a physician have a duty to report certain diseases?<BR>
Is there immunity and confidentiality associated with reporting notifiable diseases?<BR>
What are the penalties for failure to make a report?<BR>
What are the requirements for reporting active tuberculosis cases
and cases of sexually transmitted disease?<BR>
What are the requirements for testing and reporting syphilis for pregnant women?<BR>
Are physician's required to instruct persons on the prevention
and cure of sexually transmitted diseases?<BR>
Are medical records relating to sexually transmitted diseases confidential?</BLOCKQUOTE>

