<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Referral of Impaired Physicians</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY background="../pics/PARCH.GIF">
<hr>
<P>
<CENTER><B><font size=6>
Referral of Impaired Physicians<BR>
</font></B></CENTER>
<P>
<hr>
<B>
<BR>
<H2><I>
How to Help
</I></H2>
The Physicians Recovery Network (PRN), the Impaired Physicians Programs of 
MASA, is available to aid any physician whose health and/or effectiveness may be 
impaired by substance abuse, alcohol, mental or emotional illness, or personality 
disorders and allegations of sexual misconduct.
<H2><I>
What Happens When You Call
</I></H2>
Your call will be answered confidentially, respecting your anonymity.  You will 
be asked for details of the problem, names and phone numbers, etc. of others who are 
familiar with the problem.  We cannot act on anonymous reports since we must respect 
the rights of everyone involved, and we need objective data to assess the problem and 
plan the best course of action.
<H2><I>
What Happens Next
</I></H2>
Details furnished by the caller will be considered by the Medical Director and a 
Committee member, and a discreet investigation may ensue.  Other volunteers may be 
called for help to conduct interviews and gather further confidential information.  
Ultimately, an intervention team may be formed to meet with the impaired physician to 
discuss the problem and seek a commitment to contact a provider for evaluation.
</B><P>
<CENTER><H4>Back to <A HREF="PRNX.HTM" TARGET="_parent" NAME="ClickMe">Physicians Recovery Network.</A></H4></CENTER>
