<HTML>
<HEAD>
<META HTTP-EQUIV="Content-Type" CONTENT="text/html; charset=ISO-8859-1">
<TITLE>Consumer Guide to Choosing a Health Plan</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.03z">
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<P>
<SCRIPT Language = "VBScript"><!--
SUB ClickMe_OnClick()
   parent.mainup.location.href="CMEFRAM.HTM"
END SUB
--></SCRIPT><BODY BACKGROUND="../pics/PARCH.GIF">
<BR>

<P>
<CENTER><TABLE ALIGN="CENTER">
<TR><TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH=229><B><IMG SRC="../pics/BROCH.GIF"></B>
</TD><TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP" WIDTH=468><I><B>NEW! 
<BR>
</B></I><B><FONT SIZE=4>Medical Association Publishes Consumer<BR>
Guide to Choosing a Health Plan<BR>
</FONT></B>
<P>
As part of its initiative on managed care, the Medical Association's Council on Medical Service has produced a booklet that provides a step by step approach for health care consumers in selecting a health plan in today's emerging managed care environment. Entitled, <B>&quot;Balancing Quality and Costs: How to Choose the Right Health Plan&quot;</B>, the brochure is directed to patients and was devised for use through our membership in waiting room areas and other appropriate settings.
<P>
The booklet does not endorse any particular health plan or delivery system, but is provided as a public service to assist consumers with important considerations in selecting a plan while providing a glossary of terms and definitions. Information for the booklet was obtained through NCQA as well as local Alabama resources. 
<P>
Members are urged to consider the brochure for use as part of their patient communications for 1997. It is available for a nominal cost of 25 cents per copy, which covers printing and mailing. (Non-member cost is 40 cents per copy.) 
<P>
To order brochures, contact the <B>Public Relations Department</B> in Montgomery at <B>1-800-239-6272.<BR>
</B>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>
<P>
