Group ranges in age from 33 to 61. Excellent salary with competitive
benefit package, including pension and profit sharing plans. Shareholder
eligibility after two years employment, rotating emergency room
schedule with 8 physicians, modern 75 bed hospital. Located in
city of 10,000 with Robert Trent Golf Course, servicing a surrounding
population of 40,000. Forty-five minutes from city of 225,000,
125 miles from Gulf beaches. For more information call 334-382-2681.
<BR>
<BR>
<B>INTERNAL MEDICINE: </B>McGregor Medical, P.A., in Mobile, a
general internal medicine practice with four associates, is actively
seeking an additional internist to join in a young, progressive
primary care practice. Excellent first year guarantees with no
initial buy in cost required. Office has central dictation of
all records, full nursing staff, trained management, complete
lab and x-ray facilities with daily radiology overhead. We are
located in an excellent area of the city next to one of our main
hospitals. The practice offers a large and established patient
base, and above average physician income. Contact: John C. Fillingim,
Administrator, 3715 Dauphin Street, Suite 600, Mobile, Alabama
36608. 334-342-7111 FAX 334-344-2241. <BR>
<BR>
<B>INTERNAL MEDICINE: </B>Internal Medicine Associates of Tuscaloosa,
a general internal medicine practice, is interested in locating
an additional BC/BE internist to join an established three physician
practice. Supported by 600 bed hospital in family oriented community
with excellent neighborhoods and schools. Major University and
45 minutes from Birmingham, Alabama. Send CV to: Mona Humphreys,100
Rice Mine Road, Suite B, Tuscaloosa, Alabama 35406.<BR>
<BR>
<B>INTERNIST AND PEDIATRICIAN: </B>Needed for Ambulatory Care
Clinics. BC/BE. Alabama medical license. Eligible to work in the
U.S. Competitive salary and benefits. Send CV to Business Office
, 7850 S. Memorial Parkway, Huntsville, Alabama 35802.<BR>
<BR>
<B>NEPHROLOGIST BC/BE: </B>Dialysis Center seeks nephrologist
to join our National Healthcare Team in Alabama and Tennessee.
Great opportunity as Medical Director of new facilities. For more
information contact: Cynthia Whisner,1730 West Second Street,
Montgomery, Alabama 36106 334-832-4616. FAX 334-832-1094.<BR>
<BR>
<B>NEUROLOGY: </B>The Neurology Clinic, P.C, is an established
practice in the Tuscaloosa-Northport area with a population of
approximately 100,000 in the combined metropolitan area. In addition
the patient population also draws from the surrounding rural areas.
The practice provides clinical services as well as testing to
include EEG, long term video recording, EMG, NCV, EP and ultrasound.
Pleasant office space and a stable clerical and technical staff
are in place. At present, the Neurology Clinic has one board-certified
neurologist and is seeking to add one more board-certified/board-eligible
neurologist. Services are also provided in the two area hospitals.
Multiple outreach clinics are available, if desired. Financial
arrangements are negotiable, and can reach the top 5% for the
nation. The area provides pleasant living conditions and recreational
facilities. Public and private schooling are available and Tuscaloosa
is well known as the home of the University of Alabama. The University
also provides a variety of cultural events. Additional dining,
shopping and cultural events are easily accessible in nearby Birmingham
and Montgomery. For more information contact: Teresa Newborn,
Administrative Assistant or Dr. Alexandre Todorov, Neurology Clinic,
P.C., Suite 201, 1325 McFarland Blvd., Northport, Alabama 35476
or call 205-553-4684.<BR>
<BR>
<B>OB/GYN PRACTICE: </B>Five physician group practice with four
practicing OB/GYN and one practicing GYN only. Seeking a fifth
BE/BC obstetrician to join group and share equal rotation in call
schedule (one in five with every fifth weekend). The practice
is located in Dothan Alabama (southeastern part of state), a community
of 53,000 servicing an area of approximately 400,000. Dothan is
a family community with many extras such as one of the Robert
Trent Jones Golf facilities and a water park. It is 90 miles from
the Emerald Coast of Florida (Panama City, Destin) and has many
local attractions for those who enjoy outdoor activities. The
office is located in the Doctor's Office Building at Southeast
Alabama Medical Center occupying approximately 12,000 sq.ft of
prime space and within three minutes walking distance to Labor
and Delivery. The practice was established in 1982 and the patient
base continues to increase. Four day work week, guaranteed salary,
24 days vacation/CME allowance, life, health, dental, and liability
insurance in the first year. Fully funded retirement plan and
possible partnership offer after first year. Phone Administrator,
Stanley Fulford at 334-793-3900 office or 334-712-0265 home.<BR>
<BR>
<B>OB/GYN PRACTICE: </B>Busy OB/GYN practice in Opelika, Alabama
seeks an associate, board eligible or board certified. Practice
serves the Auburn-Opelika area, as well as a thirty mile radius.
Rapid growth of practice as well as attractive family-oriented
community makes this an excellent opportunity. Please contact:
Dr. Gwen Cooper, 502 E. Thomason Circle, Opelika, AL 36801 or
call 334-749-0390 if interested. <BR>
<BR>
<B>PEDIATRICS: </B>An energetic board certified or board eligible
pediatrician is needed immediately to join 2 board certified pediatricians
in a busy private practice in northeast Alabama. This practice
opportunity is located within easy reach of Atlanta, Birmingham,
Chattanooga, and popular local recreational lake and mountain
areas. The community has a population of approximately 50,000
with a referral area of approximately 250,000. A generous salary
and benefits package is offered. Interested pediatricians should
send their CV to Doctors Skelton and Goodin, 829 Riverbend Drive,
Gadsden, Alabama, 35901, or call 205-546-4611 FAX 205-546-2214.
<BR>
<BR>
<B>PEDIATRICIAN: </B>BE/BC to join 2 established Pediatricians.
Freestanding building with lab and x-ray. Two year guarantee.
Productivity bonus. Partnership after two years. Available immediately.
Level III nursery and neonatologists in city. One year locum tenen
position is available if you want a short term commitment. Reply
to: C. Allen White, M.D., 4154 Carmichael Road, Montgomery, Alabama
36106 or call 334-265-3264 home or 205-334-5959.<BR>
<BR>
<B>PHYSICIANS NEEDED: </B>Practice opportunity near Atlanta and
Birmingham. Fourteen physician multispecialty clinic seeks internal
medicine and family practice physicians for satellite clinics.
Few HMOs, 1 in 8 call and 375 bed regional hospital. Staff clinic
8 a.m. - 5:00 p.m., 40 hours per week. Good schools, low crime,
mountains and a university. Salary $120,000 plus performance incentives
and liberal benefits. Candidates must have completed 3 years residency,
must be Board Certified or Board Eligible, must be able to obtain
an Alabama license and must be eligible for permanent employment
in the United States. Send resume to Mike Limerick, P.O. Box 2127,
Anniston, Alabama 36202.<BR>
<BR>
<B>PRIMARY CARE PHYSICIANS: </B>Opportunities to practice medicine
are available at the Alabama Primary Health Care Association's
network of health centers. The Alabama Primary Health Care Association
(APHCA), is a network of 19 health care organizations operating
76 ambulatory primary care clinics in 39 urban and rural counties
of Alabama. APHCA's network of health centers offers: hassle free
management without the overhead costs; guaranteed competitive
salary; generous fringe benefits and excellent incentive package;
in-house lab, x-ray and modern equipment, experienced administrative
and medical support staff; paid vacation/holidays/cme expenses,
health, professional liability, life insurance, and coverage is
provided; plus opportunity to network with other physician colleagues.
APHCA has an on-going relationship with the state medical schools
residency programs, and the Tuskegee Area Health Education Center.
Continuing Medical Education is available through workshops planned
by the Clinical Directors' network. Teaching and research are
explorable oppportunities. If you want to practice medicine where
you are MOST NEEDED, JOIN APHCA'S NETWORK OF HEALTH CENTERS WHERE
YOU WILL BE MOST WELCOMED! For more information call 334-271-7068.
<BR>
<BR>
<B>RADIOLOGY: </B>Radiology associate wanted for progressive North
Mississippi City of 15,000. New hospital renovation including
X-Ray Dept. New color ultrasound, spect gamma camera, GE Highlight
advantage CT and mobile GE 0.5 Signa MR. Excellent recreation
(boating, fishing, hunting, golf, tennis etc.) Good schools. FAX
601-226-3419. <BR>
<P>
<B>UROLOGIST: </B>To join another Urologist in Northern Alabama.
