<B><CENTER><FONT FACE="Times New Roman" SIZE=4>&quot;Managed Care in Alabama&quot;--Annual
Session 1996<BR>
</CENTER></FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">A videotape summary of discussions
on managed care that were conducted as part of the educational
sessions at the Medical Association's 135th Annual Session, April
19-21, at the Perdido Resort, Orange Beach, Alabama, is available
upon request.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Included: <I>Evaluating Managed
Care Contracts--Practical Suggestions</I>, featuring comments
from W. Stancil Starnes, Esquire, with Starnes &amp; Atchison,
Birmngham;</FONT>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">and John Mooresmith, Esquire, with
Burr &amp; Foreman, Birmingham.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<U><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"><I><B>Alabama Perspectives on
Managed Care</B></I>,</FONT></U><FONT FACE="Times New Roman"> featuring
remarks from Becky S. Holliman, Executive Director, Prime Health;
James R. Ludwig, CEO, Health Partners of Alabama; Bob Suellentrop,
President &amp; CEO, United Healthcare South; and Gene Thrasher,
President, Blue Cross/Blue Shield of Alabama.<BR>
</FONT>
<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<FONT FACE="Helvetica" SIZE=4>For more information or to obtain a
copy of the video, contact:<BR>
MASA Public Relations<BR>
1-800-239-6272</CENTER></FONT></B><P>
