<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../pics/PARCH.GIF">
<HR>
<P>
<CENTER></P><B><FONT SIZE=4>ALABAMA INSTITUTIONS AND ORGANIZATIONS
ACCREDITED<BR>
FOR CONTINUING MEDICAL EDUCATION THROUGH THE<BR>
ACCREDITATION COUNCIL FOR CONTINUING MEDICAL EDUCATION (ACCME)</P></FONT></B></CENTER>
<HR>
<P>
</P><B>Listed below are Alabama-based organizations whose CME
programs have been carefully reviewed and approved as meeting
the educational standards of the <I>Essentials of Accreditation
of the ACCME</I>. They may therefore designate CME activities
as meeting the criteria for Category 1 of the AMA Physician's
Recognition Award.<BR>
</P></B>
<P>
<B>They are an excellent resource to you as a nearby location
to participate in Category 1 activities. Please check with the
organization's Director of Medical Education or Education Committee
for details on scheduled meetings available to you.<BR>
</P></B>
<P>
<B>If you are a member of a hospital staff or medical organization
that has not been accredited but does plan and present CME programs,
they may also be willing to serve as a joint sponsor, thereby,
offering the possibility of CME credit for your offerings.<BR>
</P></B>
<P>
<B>Please contact the MASA Education Department at 1-800-239-6272
or 334-263-6441 if you need further information on these organizations
or on accreditation procedures.<BR>
</P></B>
<P>
<CENTER><B>ACCREDITED DIRECTLY BY THE ACCME <BR>
(Organization based in Alabama)</B> </P></CENTER>
