<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Home Management</TITLE><BASE TARGET="_top">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../pics/PARCH.GIF">
<CENTER><H2>Financial and Home Management WWW Sites</H2></CENTER>
<B><I><BLOCKQUOTE>The list below is provided only as starting points for some of the most oft requested information that affects your everyday life.  Indeed, pages could be devoted to each category but our intention here is to get the beginner access to a few of the most informative sites on the Web.</BLOCKQUOTE></I>
<H3>Investing</H3>
<A HREF="http://cnnfn.com">CNNfn </A>- A daily review of the day's business and market news as well as a personalized finance area.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.investools.com">INVESTools </A>- Over thirty popular financial newsletters which are available for purchase.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.brill.com">Mutual Funds Interactive </A>- Expert commentary and basics of fund investing.<P>
<A HREF="http://networth.galt.com">NETworth </A>- An excellent investment research tool.<P>
<H3>Yields and Rates</H3>
<A HREF="http://www.bankrate.com">Bank Rate Monitor Infobank </A>- The latest deals in 70 cities for consumer loans, mortgages, home-equity lines, credit cards, CDs and money-market accounts.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.ramresearch.com">RAM Research Group </A>- Lists of good no-fee and low-rate credit cards, rebate cards, secured cards, and credit union cards.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.financenter.com">Financenter </A>- Over twenty financial calculators aid you in evaluating different scenarios involving your house, car, and credit cards.<P>
<H3>Charities</H3>
<A HREF="http://www.give.org">National Charities Information Bureau </A>- The citizens' watchdog on charitable organizations' ethical practices.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.clark.net/pub/pwalker/home.html">The Nonprofit Resources Catalog </A>- Links to non-profit related sites.<P>
<H3>Daily News</H3>
<A HREF="http://www.panamnet.net/explorer/news.html">Pan AmNet Explorer</A>- An excellent set of links to multiple major news wires, many of which are updated every thirty minutes.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.nytimesfax.com/altfax.html">The New York Times </A>- You will need the Acrobat or Envoy software preinstalled to make use of this site, though a hyperlink is provided to obtain evaluation copies.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.usatoday.com/psd1.htm">USA Today </A><P>
<H3>Insurance</H3>
<A HREF="http://www.insure.com">Insurance News Network </A>- How to choose auto, home and life insurance and check out how insurers size up in ability to pay claims.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.iiaa.iix.com/default.htm">Independent Insurance Network </A>- as above with tips for dealing with natural disasters and filing claims.<P>
<H3>Automobiles</H3>
<A HREF="http://www.edmunds.com">Edmund's Automobile Buyer's Guide </A>- Better than the Blue Book for buying automobiles (I accessed this before buying my wife's Accord!).<P>
<A HREF="http://www.nhtsa.dot.gov">National Highway Traffic Safety Administration </A>- Check out a car's history of consumer complaints and recalls before buying.<P>
<H3>Home</H3>
<A HREF="http://www1.mhv.net/~dfriedman/ashihome.htm#buyers">American Society of Home Inspectors </A>- Anticipate your prospective home's problems before you buy as well as search for local home inspectors certified by ASHI.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.homefair.com">Homebuyer's Fair </A>- Homebuying tips, mortgage calculators and cost-of-living differences between cities.<P>
<A HREF="http://homescout.com">HomeScout </A>- Searches over 300,000 home listings after you enter your specific criteria.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.owners.com">The Owners Network </A>- Home owners wishing to sell their house without an agent can post a listing here, including a photo if desired.<P>
<H3>Travel</H3>
<A HREF="http://www.coolworks.com/showme">Cool Works </A>- Paid and volunteer, seasonal and full-time job opportunities in a variety of exotic places, such as cruise ships, ski resorts, and national parks.  Ideal for your adolescent looking to gain valuable work experience away from home.<P>  
<A HREF="http://www.travelocity.com">Travelocity </A>- Search the best itinerary and cheapest airfares for travel around the world as well as leads on lodging, restaurants, nightlife, festivals and kids' activities.<P>
<H3>Consumer Watchdogs</H3>
<A HREF="http://www.bbb.org">The Better Business Bureau </A>- The time honored advisory service online.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.fraud.org">National Fraud Information Center </A>- Report suspected telemarketing and internet fraud here and obtain tips on how to avoid scamsters.<P>
<H3>Government</H3>
<A HREF="http://www.ustreas.gov/treasury/bureaus/pubdebt">Bureau of Public Debt </A>- Information on Treasury auctions, U.S. savings bonds, Treasury bills and bonds.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.irs.ustreas.gov/prod/cover.html">Internal Revenue Service </A>- Everything you ever wanted to know and the forms you need via an unusually unboring format.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.ssa.gov">Social Security Online </A>- Get an estimate of your social security benefits (while they last) or information on benefits programs.<P>
<H3>College Planning</H3>
<A HREF="http://www.collegenet.com">CollegeNET </A>- Research data bases of universities and even community colleges as you prepare for your childrens' future.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.finaid.org">FinAid, The Financial Aid Information Page </A>- Not only a good tool for estimating need but access to nearly 200,000 scholarship programs and links to college financial-aid offices.<P>
<H3>Family</H3>
<A HREF="http://www.ice.net/~kstevens/ELDERWEB.HTM">Eldercare Web </A>- Resources for the elderly and their caregivers.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.kidscamp.com">Kids' Camp </A>- Plan your child's summer and even find family camps and tours.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.nannytax.com">NannyTax </A>- Avoid getting trapped in federal and state laws when hiring household help.<P>
<A HREF="http://www.nolo.com">Nolo Press Self-Help Law Center </A>- Advice on many matters too broad and comprehensive to do justice to it here.</B><P><HR>

<CENTER><b><I>This site is growing and we need your help!</CENTER><P>
If you know of any important web sites or find any of these links to be broken,
please mail the webmaster directly by sending Email to <a href="mailto:frisbie@quicklink.net">frisbie@quicklink.net.</a>
Include the name of the site and a brief description and we will post changes as quickly as possible.</I></b><P>
<CENTER><B>Click <a href=../INTERNET.HTM TARGET="mainup">here</a> to return to the Internet Sites document</B></CENTER>

