<HEAD><H1>AMA-YPS PUBLICATIONS LIST</H1>
<TITLE>AMA-YPS Publications</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<I>The following publications are available at no cost from the AMA Department of the Young Physician Services.</I><P>
<UL><LI><B><I>NEW!</I>  Guide to AMA Services and Resources for Young Physicians Entering Practice - </B>describes services to help physicians as they enter practice.  Includes resources on managed care, practice management, career resources, continuing education.</LI><BR>
<LI><B><I>NEW!</I>  Getting Involved in YOUR AMA - </B>discusses opportunities for involvement on the AMA Board, on councils and committees, and in other positions of leadership.</LI><BR>
<LI><B><I>NEW!</I>  Violence Prevention in the Medical Workplace:  Prevention Strategies - </B>information on violence predictors, personal precautions, risk assessment/management, and institutional security.  Includes model protocols, legislative and legal information, policy statements, institutional standards, addresses of other organizations, and annotated bibliographies.</LI><BR>
<LI><B>Contracts:  What You Need to Know - </B>a comprehensive resource publication.  Includes sample contracts, tips on contracting, finding legal counsel, and where to get further information.</LI><BR>
<LI><B>How Medical Democracy Determines Policy:  A Primer - </B>information on the AMA and the YPS; basic information on policy development:  writing AND formatting resolutions, caucus participation, running for election, and testifying at reference committee hearings.</LI><BR>
<LI><B>A Compendium of Position Statements - </B>a chronology and summary of all YPS policies that have been ratified by the Assembly since its inception.</LI><BR>
<LI><B>Directory of Federation Contacts and Programs for Young Physicians - </B>comprehensive information about the level and nature of young physician involvement and participation throughout the Federation.</LI><BR>
<LI><B>Young Physicians Section Outreach Program - </B>a peer recruitment program whereby young physicians solicit AMA members; awards are given at June YPS Assembly meeting.</LI><BR>
<LI><B>YPS Fact Sheet - </B>provides data on practice modes, gender, board certification and specialties of physicians under age 40.</LI></UL><P>
