<HTML><BODY BACKGROUND="../pics/PARCH.GIF"><CENTER><a name="TOP"><img src="../pics/YPSLOGO.GIF" align=bottom width=349 height=113></a></CENTER>
<HEAD><CENTER><H1>AMA-YPS SERVICES AND RESOURCES</H1></CENTER>
<TITLE>AMA-YPS Services</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<I>Most services are provided at no cost to members of the American Medical Association.</I><P><P>
<TAB INDENT=6><b>Young physicians starting a practice will enter a confusing world of complicated contract agreements, physician payment protocols, and treatment guidelines.
  These issues can be overwhelming and the AMA provides the resources to help you get started in the right direction.</b>
<P><I><B>Click on an area of interest below or <a href="YPS.HTM" TARGET="main" NAME="ClickMe">here</a> to return to the MASA-YPS main menu.</B></I>
<H3><DL>
<DT><a href=#mc>Managed Care</a>
<DT><a href=#CLP>Contracts and Legal Pitfalls</a>
<DT><a href=#pm>Practice Management</a>
<DT><a href=#pr>Practice Resources</a>
<DT><a href=#pp>Physician Payment</a>
<DT><a href=#pg>Practice Guidelines</a>
<DT><A HREF=#mpp>Medical Practice Profiles</A>
<DT><A HREF=#in>Insurance</A>
<DT><A HREF=#ce>Continuing Education (CME)</A>
<DT><A HREF=#fa>Financial Assistance</A>
<DT><A HREF=#pcr>Professional Career Resources</A>
<DT><A HREF=#pgu>Physician Guidelines</A>
<DT><A HREF=#rm>Risk Management</A>
</H3></DL><P> <P><HR>
<CENTER><A NAME="mc"><i><h2>Managed Care</h2></i></a></CENTER><UL>
<LI><b>AMA Doctors Advisory Network </b>- For members only. &nbsp;The network is a select group of physicians, lawyers and business consultants who are experts in managed care.  You'll talk with a member of AMA's legal department who will assess
your needs and refer you to qualified individuals from our database of managed care experts.  <B>Contact</B> 1-800-262-1066.<P>
<LI><b>The Physician and Managed Care </b>- The foundation for a clear understanding of managed care and how it will affect your practice. Includes information on national trends affecting the industry and a plan for adapting your practice to managed care.  <B>Contact</B> 1-800-621-8335; order #OP637393MJ<P>
<LI><b>Doctors Resource Service </b>- These publications cover virtually every aspect of today's rapidly evolving health care system, from compensation systems to delivery models, from legal issues to ethical concerns. <B>Contact</B> 1-800-262-1066<P><ul type=square>
<LI><b><i>Issue 1 </i></b> - <u>An Overview of Managed Care</u> reviews managed care principles, private and group practice options, legal rights and obligations, utilization review, and contract negotiations.<P>
<Li><b><i>Issue 2 </i></b> - <u>Forming PHOs and Integrated Networks</u> discusses PHOs from the physician viewpoint, different PHO models, plans for organizing and financing a PHO, and negotiation
processes with payers to assure conformity with antitrust laws.<P>
<li><b><i>Issue 3 </i></b> - <u>Negotiating and Contracting</u> analyzes negotiation and contracting skills in detail, far-reaching antitrust and personal liability risks, patient grievance procedures, utilization
and quality review, financial audits, physician rights under dispute resolution, and 
potentially dangerous contract provisions.<P>
<li><b><i>Issue 4 </i></b> - <u>Compensation Arrangements</u> details risks and rewards of pre-paid capitation contracts, discounted reimbursement, fee withholds, contract proposals for financial viability,
updating protocols, cost efficiencies by redistributing non-clinical tasks, and relationships between primary care and specialty physicians.<P>
<li><b><i>Issue 5 </i></b> - <u>Evaluating Your Practice</u> outlines methods of valuation, cash flow analysis, market and regulatory position of the practice, present value formulas, sources of capital, 
"too-sweet" deals, protection of personal assets from attachment to loans, and fraud and abuse laws avoidance.<p>
<li><b><i>Issue 6 </i></b> - <u>Demonstrating Clinical Efficiency</u> discusses cost-effective care, theory and 
practice of utilization review, use of outcomes studies, patient satisfaction 
measurements, actual-to-expected review criteria, and peer review conundrum.<p>
<li><b><i>Issue 7 </i></b> - <u>Law and Strategy</u> reviews legal mine fields created by managed 
care, contractual redress, liability risks, physician risks under HMO insolvency, and antitrust and ERISA violations.<p>
<li><b><i>Issue 8 </i></b> - <u>Gatekeeper-Specialists Relationship</u> details territorial dispute resolution between physicians, ethics and the effects of financial incentives, use of risk pools, 
and appropriate mix and number of specialists for given patient populations.<P>
<li><b><i>Issue 9 </i></b>- <u>Physicians Responding to Change</u> analyzes response to termination, move from patient advocate to care manager, physician retraining, including self-assessment model for deciding next steps.</UL><P>
<li><b>Negotiation and Contracting in Managed Care </b>- This set of four softbound booklets provides practical information on legal, financial, and business matters associated with managed care.&nbsp; <B>Contact</B> 1-800-621-8335; OP#637193MJ. &nbsp;The set includes:<P><ul type=square>
<li><b><i>A Physicians' Guide to Managed Care Contracting. </i></b>&nbsp; How to read and interpret a standard managed care contract.
<li><b><i>Financial Aspects of Managed Care Contracting. </i></b>&nbsp; Negotiate the optimum financial situation for yourself.
<li><b><i>Antitrust and Managed Care. </i></b>&nbsp; Avoid legal pitfalls by understanding antitrust laws as they apply to the managed care field.
<li><b><i>Establishing a Physician Organization. </i></b>&nbsp; A helpful introduction for physicians considering a physician organization. 
&nbsp;Includes sample contracts and agreements.</UL> 
