<CENTER><A NAME="rm"><I><h3>Risk Management</h3></I></A></CENTER>
<ul>
<li><B>Medical Practice Risk Manager </B>- This newsletter is committed to helping you and your staff establish systems and procedures that will enhance patient care and help reduce liability risk.  Features 
in-depth articles written by experts on risk management issues.  Includes sample forms, 
checklists, protocols, self-assessment quizzes, and other practical tools for reducing 
risk. In addition, each issue addresses regulatory and legislative issues of current 
issues. <B>Contact</B> 1-800-621-8335; Order #NR638094NW<p>
<li><B>Risk Factors in Medical Practice Video </B>- Learn field-tested liability reducing techniques and gain a better understanding of the medical-legal impact of poor communication. Poor communication is often a factor
in peer review complaints and litigation. A video workshop teaches you practical techniques
for improving your patient and office communication skills. A workbook contains exercises 
that take you through a step-by-step training process that teaches you how to identify 
and solve communication problems.  <B>Contact</B> 1-800-621-8335; Order #637894NW <p>
<li><B>Risk Management Principles & Commentaries </B>- Apply standard risk management principles to non-clinical aspects of your medical practice. Emphasis is placed on communications and office administrative systems. <B>Contact</B> 1-800-621-8335; Order #630190NW<p>
<li><B>Grand Rounds of Medical Malpractice </B>- Your resource on medical liability and risk management.  A "grand rounds" approach examines basic topics in medical liability: the physician/patient relationship, 
negligence, informed consent, adverse outcomes, physician impairment, professional 
liability insurance, and peer review.  Each chapter includes a case scenario, a 
thorough exposition of the topic, discussion questions, articles reprinted
from the current literature, and an annotated bibliography.  CME credit is available.
<B>Contact</B> 1-800-621-8335; Order #630690NW<p>
</ul><CENTER>Return to the <a href="#TOP">Main Menu</a>.</CENTER> 
