<HEAD>

<TITLE>Workshops and Conferences</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="maslin33.jpg">
<B><CENTER><H2>WORKSHOPS AND CONFERENCES</H2>

<table border=6 cellpadding=0><tr><td>
<img border=0 src="hilal1.jpg"></tr></table>

During the conference: International Relations in the post-Cold War
World
</CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE><I><P ALIGN="right">
			According to a legend, the Mediterranean reaches as far
			as the olive trees can grow. According to the other,
			olive is the tree of peace.
			Biologists consider it one of the longest-lived "beings".
			As a symbol, it sublimes space, time and ideal.<P>
</I></BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR noshade>
<H3>COLLOQUIA AND CONFERENCES</H3>
<OL>
<LI>The Mediterranean: Bridge or Divide (Colloquium), May 1991

<LI>Neutrality and Non-Alignement in the Post-Cold War Era (Colloquium),
 November 1991<BR>
<A HREF="#publications">(See publication no. 1)</A>

<LI>The Legal Protection of the Environment beyond the Limits of National
 Jurisdiction (Colloquium), May 1992
<A HREF="#publications">(See publication no. 2)</A>

<LI><A HREF="northsou/madsnort.htm">North-South relations in the Mediterranean 
(Colloquium)</A>, November 1992

<LI>Strengthening of Foreign Ministries in transition, 1992.<BR>
</B>UN Meeting in which the Academy has been involved.<B>

<LI>Confidence-Building in the Middle East (Expert-group meeting), April 1994.
</B>Organised with UNIDIR.<B>

<LI>Track meeting in support of the multilateral 
negotiations on arms control (ACRS) in the Middle East,<BR> June 1994.<BR>
</B>Organised in cooperation with the Henry L. Stimson Center (Washington, D.C.). 
This informal meeting brought together high-level delegations from various 
Mediterranean, North African and Middle Eastern States.<B>

<LI>International Relations Five Years After the End of the Cold War (Seminar),
 October 1994.<BR>
<A HREF="#publications" >(See publication no. 4)</A><BR>
</B>Organised in collaboration with the Center of International Studies, Princeton 
University The Seminar was organized in the context of the World Order Models 
Project (WOMP). As a result of this meeting the Academy has been asked to 
become a representative of the WOMP for the Mediterranean region.<B>

<LI>New Approach for International Environmental Law and Diplomacy: Global
Partnership and the Mediterranean Model, 29th February - 2nd March, 1996.<BR>
</B>Organised in cooperation with The Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Malta and
The Institute of International Affairs.<B>

<LI>
<A HREF="abarcel/welcome.htm">An International Colloquium: Cooperation and Security in the Mediterranean:
 Prospects After Barcelona</A>, March 1996.

<LI>
<A HREF="chemic/medsite.htm">Regional Seminar on the Chemical Weapons Convention
and its National Implementation</A></B><BR>
Meeting in which the Academy has been involved.

</OL> 

<HR noshade>
<H3>WORKSHOPS</H3>
<OL>
<LI>Training Needs of Palestinian Diplomacy, November 1992

<LI>Computer Applications in Diplomacy, January 1994.<BR></B>
 This workshop was jointly sponsored by the United Nations and the Maltese
 Ministry of Foreign Affairs. In addition to the Academy's students,
 Foreign Ministry representatives from over ten countries attended the
 Workshop.<B>

<LI>Efficiency in Negotiation, February 1995.</B><BR>
 Workshop was conducted by <B>Dr. Robert Weibel</B>, consultant and trainer, Geneva.<B>  
<LI><A HREF="cad95/workshop.htm">Use of Information Technology in International
 Relations</A>, 20th November - 1st December 1995.</B><BR>
Organised by: Mediterranean Academy of Diplomatic Studies, 
Commonwealth Network of IT for Development (COMNET-IT)
in collaboration with Multilateral Affairs Directorate, Ministry of
 Foreign Affairs of Malta and The Management and Training Services
 Division, Commonwealth Secretariat.<B>
<LI>Negotiating (with)in the European Union, March 1996.</B><BR>
Seminar conducted by <B>Mr. Paul W. Meerts</B>, Deputy Director, Netherlands
Institute of International Relations.<B>
</OL>

