<HEAD>

<TITLE>PROJECT PROPOSAL</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=5>DIPLOMACY@INFORMATION.TECHNOLOGY</FONT></B>
<P>
<CENTER><I><FONT SIZE=4>Networking Project</FONT></I></CENTER>
<HR>

<P>
<A HREF="Summary.htm" >Summary</A><BR>

<P>
<I>founding partners<BR>
</I>
<P>
<A HREF="../dsp/default.htm"><B><FONT SIZE=2>Diplomatic Studies Programme </FONT></B></A><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">of
<A HREF="http://www.hei.unige.ch"><B>the Graduate Institute of International Studies </B></A><B>in
Geneva, Switzerland</B></FONT></B>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.comnet.mt"><B>Commonwealth Network of Information Technology for Development (COMNET-IT)</B></A><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">,
Malta<BR>
</FONT></B>
<P>
<I>coordination</I>
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.diplomacy.edu"><B>Mediterranean Academy of Diplomatic Studies</B></A><B>,
University of Malta, Malta</B>
<HR>

<P>
<B><FONT FACE="Arial">CONTENTS<BR>
</FONT></B>
<OL>
<LI><A HREF="#genesis"><B><FONT SIZE=2>Genesis of the Project</FONT></B></A>
<LI><A HREF="#objectives"><B><FONT SIZE=2>Objectives of the Project</FONT></B></A>
<LI><A HREF="#description"><B><FONT SIZE=2>Activities</FONT></B></A>
<BR>

</OL>

<HR>

<P>
<A NAME="genesis"><B><FONT SIZE=2>1. GENESIS OF THE PROJECT</FONT></B></A>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The Mediterranean Academy of Diplomatic
Studies is the last of a series of regional centers of diplomatic
training and studies set up by the Geneva Graduate Institute of
International Studies. The other institutions are in Trinidad,
Cameroon and Kenya.</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Being the most recent creation, our
Academy has from the outset striven to use the most advanced means
and methods available for office work, training, research and
documentation. For improving these efforts, the Academy established
in 1993 an Unit for Computer Applications in Diplomacy. The major
objective is to equip diplomats with proper conceptual and methodological
skills for working in the post-Cold War international environment,
that is increasingly influenced by information technology.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The Unit has performed the following
major activities over the last 3 years:<BR>
</FONT>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="../unit/ITcourse/introduc.htm">Course in Information Technology and Diplomacy</A><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">
(3 generations of the Academy's students who are junior diplomats
from Mediterranean countries have been trained in IT and Diplomacy);
</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Workshop on Computer Applications
in Diplomacy - January 1994 for Ministries of Foreign Affairs
from former Soviet Union and Eastern Europe.</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The development of a Model of Computerisation
of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs; the Model was partly implemented
in Malta's Ministry of Foreign Affairs; it was presented at the
UN Meeting on Strengthening Foreign Ministries in Transition (June
1993).</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The creation of a Database of International
Legal Instruments; database contains complete data (text, basic
information, list of countries that signed and ratified convention,
texts of reservations, etc.) for more than 2000 international
conventions and other international instruments; the database
has been used in Malta's Ministry of Foreign Affairs.</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">The development of Computer-assisted
learning (CAL) package for Diplomacy. The CAL package is based
on hypermedia. Demo-version has been used during the last academic
year by students at the Academy (postgraduate course in Diplomacy).</FONT>

</UL>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Following the positive experience and
achieved results at the Mediterranean Academy of Diplomatic Studies,
the Diplomatic Studies Programme of the Graduate Institute of
International Studies with support of the Swiss Development Corporation
decided to promote this Programme to sister institutes in Nairobi,
Yaounde and St.Augustine.<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
<HR>

<P>
<A NAME="objectives"><B><FONT SIZE=2>2. OBJECTIVES <BR>
</FONT></B></A>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">General Objectives<BR>
</FONT></B>
<UL>
<LI>Increasing efficiency - reducing the cost of diplomatic activities
<BR>

</UL>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=2>Developing countries, especially those with limited
financial and human resources, find it difficult to meaningfully
participate in today's intensive multilateral and bilateral diplomatic
activities which increasingly tackles issues that have great impact
on national interests and policies. Moreover, maintaining diplomatic
network is a big financial and organizational burden for most
of the developing states. The development of Information Technology
(IT) makes diplomatic activities less costly but more effective.
Thus the ultimate objective of our Project is to help developing
countries to conduct their diplomatic activities with reduce cost
and increased efficiency.<BR>
</FONT>
<UL>
<LI>Increasing IT-awareness in developing countries<BR>

</UL>

<P>
<FONT SIZE=1 FACE="Arial">Programme is based on comprehensive
approach to IT focusing not only on use of computers but also
on legal, social and other consequences of the development of
IT (protection of intellectual property). Thus Programme will
increase the IT-culture and awareness among students, diplomats
and others involved in diplomatic activities</FONT><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">.
<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Institutional Objectives<BR>
</FONT></B>
<UL>
<LI>Capacity-building of the sister academies and institutes in
Kenya, Trinidad and Tobago, Cameroon, Malta and Switzerland;
<LI>Integrated Management of academic and human resources of sister
academies and institutes;
<LI>Automation of administrative work;
<LI>Promoting computer-based learning;
<LI>Promoting distance learning<BR>

</UL>

<HR>

<P>
<A NAME="description"><B><FONT SIZE=2>3. ACTIVITIES <BR>
</FONT></B></A>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Preparatory activities </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">-
performed at the Mediterranean Academy of Diplomatic Studies<BR>
</FONT>
<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Preparation of detailed and comprehensive
Project with all technical and organisational aspects;</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Survey of existing equipment and
expertise at institutes as well as of networking possibilities
(Internet, etc.);</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Preparation of teaching materials
for courses for administrative staff, academic staff and students
that should be performed during the first visit to institutes;</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Preparation of new software packages
or adaptation of existing packages for automatization of administrative
and secretarial activities at institutes;</FONT>
<LI><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Creation of home-pages (World Wide
Web), listserv mailing lists and other Internet services that
will be used for networking purposes;<BR>
</FONT>
</UL>

<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Arial">Major activities<BR>
</FONT></B>
<P>
