</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=66><FONT SIZE=1 FACE="Arial">Establishment of Units or Center for IT and Diplomacy in all institutes and academies;</FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH=86><FONT SIZE=1 FACE="Arial">Parallel with computeristion of institutes there will be a need to establish organisational structures that will enable sustainability and further utilisation of achieved capacity and expertise. Organizational structure should be based on Units or Centers for IT and Diplomacy with main task to further promote computerisation of diplomatic activities in particular regions (Nairobi - East Africa; Yaounde - West Africa; Trinidad and Tobago - Carribian region; Malta - Mediterranean region and Central Europe). These Units/Centers should take also electronic publishing activities of materials important for those regions. </FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH=62><FONT SIZE=1>Unit for IT and Diplomacy (established in 1993) as a part of the Academy</FONT>
</TD><TD COLSPAN=2 WIDTH=123><FONT SIZE=1>Center for IT and Diplomacy (established in 1996) by agreement between Institute and local private company.</FONT>
