<TITLE>Degree Programmes</TITLE>
<HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="spiral.jpg">

<B><H2>DEGREE PROGRAMMES</H2>
<P>
The Mediterranean Academy offers to diplomats and other government
officials a post-graduate curriculum extending over a period of
an academic year. In fulfillment of all requirements, the diplomats
will receive a Master in Diplomacy (M.Dip.). Given the strong
demands for diplomatic studies by university students from Malta
and abroad, the Academy also offers a course for a Master of Arts
in Diplomatic Studies (M.A.), a course for a Certificate in Diplomatic
Studies and a course for a Diploma in Diplomatic Studies. The
M.Dip. and M.A. degrees are internationally recognised university
degrees, awarded by the University of Malta.
<P>
MASTER IN DIPLOMACY (M. Dip.)
<P>
The programme for a Master in Diplomacy lasts 9 months and is
open to diplomats and other government officials from Mediterranean
countries. The candidates must be nominated by their government
and be in possession of an university degree that satisfies equivalency
requirements of the University of Malta. Furthermore, they should
have served for at least one year in a diplomatic capacity and
be fluent in English.
<P>
The curriculum includes classes in Diplomacy, International Relations,
International Economics, International History and International
Law. Candidates for the M.Dip. shall attend 2 one-semester courses
in all of these fields. Award of the degree is based on course
work, a major research paper and an end-of-year examination.
<P>
MASTER OF ARTS IN DIPLOMATIC STUDIES (M.A.)
<P>
The course for the Master of Arts in Diplomatic Studies lasts
one year. Candidates must be holders of a first degree with
at least second class honours or its equivalent.<P>

The curriculum includes classes in International Relations, International
Economics, International History and International Law. Requirements include completion of coursework (16 credits), pass final examination, and completion
of a dissertation of maximum 40,000 words. Award of the degree is based on the
successful completion of the above requirements.

<P>
CERTIFICATE AND DIPLOMA IN DIPLOMATIC STUDIES
<P>
The courses for the Certificate and the Diploma in Diplomatic
Studies are part-time evening courses. The Certificate is a one-year
course concentrating on International Relations, International
Economics and International Law. Holders of the Certificate are
entitled to pursue additional studies to obtain the Diploma in
Diplomatic Studies during the second year, whereby they will attend
seminars on selected topics of International Law, International
Economics and International Relations. Candidates for the Certificate
(first-year) must satisfy admission requirements of the University
of Malta. Candidates for the Diploma in Diplomatic Studies (second-year)
must be holder of the Certificate. Assessment for both courses
will be based on coursework, a research paper and an end-of-year
examination.
<P>
</B>
<HR>
