<TITLE>Registration and Practical Information</TITLE>
<HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="spiral.jpg">

<CENTER><B><H2>REGISTRATION AND PRACTICAL INFORMATION</H2>
<P>
Registration</CENTER>
<P>
Registration for the M.Dip. and M.A. courses is upon admission
by the University Board of Admission. Applications for the M.Dip.
have to be submitted to the Director of the Academy by Ministries
of Foreign Affairs or Embassies accredited to Malta. M.A. candidates
should send applications to the Director of the International
Office, University of Malta, Tal-Qroqq, Msida MSD 06, Malta. On
registration, candidates must submit the original documents of
their degrees.
<P>
Registration fees for those M.Dip. students who have been granted
a scholarship (see below) will be covered by the Academy. Registration
fees for the M.A. programme must be paid by non-Maltese students.
The amount is &#163;m 800 per academic year. Registration fees for the
Diploma course must be paid by all and amount to &#163;m 15 per semester
for Maltese students and &#163;m 150 per semester for non-Maltese students.
<P>
<CENTER>Important Dates</CENTER>
<P>
The deadline of application for the M.A &amp; M.Dip. Courses for
the 1996/97 Academic Year is 31st July, 1996 for Maltese applicants,
31st May, 1996 for non-Maltese applicants.
<P>
The Academic Year begins 1st October, 1996 and ends 30th June, 1997.
<P>
<CENTER>Cost of living in Malta</CENTER>
<P>
A foreign student should expect lodging expenses of &#163;m 80-120
a month and other living expenses of &#163;m 100-130.<P>
Exchange rate for Maltese lira (pound) is approx.: &#163;m 1 = UK pound 1.75
<P>
<CENTER>Scholarships</CENTER>
<P>
Each year a number of scholarships are available for diplomats
from the Mediterranean region. For more information, please contact
the Secretariat.
<P>
</B>
</BODY>

