</HEAD>
<TITLE>Institutional Contacts</TITLE>
<HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="spiral.jpg">

<B><H2>INSTITUTIONAL CONTACTS</H2>
<P>
The Academy has begun to establish a network of relationships
with similar institutions in the Mediterranean region and worldwide.
Formal and informal agreements were concluded with the Institute
of Diplomatic Studies of the Egyptian Ministry of Foreign Affairs,
the Association des Etudes Internationales in Tunis, the Istituto
Affari Internazionali in Rome, the Istituto Diplomatico of the
Italian Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Escuela Diplomatica
of the Spanish Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
<P>
The common objective is to exchange visiting lecturers and to
organize joint courses, seminars and colloquia. In the context
of institutional contacts, the Academy has been able to visit
together with the M.Dip students other institutions abroad. In
1993, a visit was made to the Mediterranean Action Plan (Athens)
and in 1994 to Tunis for a special seminar on &quot;Arab Diplomacy&quot;.
The Academy also has joined the Association of Diplomatic Academies
and Institutes of International Relations which meets once a year.
These meetings provide opportunities for the Directors of the
Geneva Graduate Institute of International Studies, the Institutes
of Trinidad, Yaounde, Nairobi, and the Academy to meet and discuss
joint endeavours such as the setting up of a computer network
among them and the launching of joint publications.
<P>
</B>
<HR>
</BODY>
</HTML>

</DOC>
