<HEAD>

<TITLE>Our Home - Palazzo Parisio</TITLE>

</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#fdf3d8">

<CENTER>
<H1><FONT COLOR="#ff8844">Our Home - Palazzo Parisio
</FONT></H1></CENTER>


<FONT SIZE=6>M</FONT>altese Ministry of Foreign Affairs is situated in one of the old palaces
that belongs to a rich heritage of the capital city Valletta. The
history of Palazzo Parsio, as the palace is called after the family
that owned it in 18th and 19th century, is as interesting as a 
historical novel. Its architecture, inner mural decorations, and
the collection of paintings can be delight for every art lover.
In that beautiful and aestethical milieu Maltese foreign affairs 
is continuing, in the modern times influenced more
and more with the growing importance of Information Technology,
the glorious traditions of diplomacy of the Order of St. John.<BR><BR>

We are cordialy inviting you to enter the two and a half centuries
long hypermedia story of Palazzo Parisio, its famous inhabitants
and historical conotations, and explore an electronic exhibition of 
its decorations, paintings and architectural design.<P>

<CENTER>
<img border=2 src="stripe11.jpg"><BR>
<B><A HREF="history/frame1.htm">The History of Palazzo Parisio</A>

<BR>
<P>
<img border=2 src="stripe22.jpg"><BR>
<B><A HREF="art/list1.htm">Art and Architecture of Palazzo Parisio</A>
</CENTER>


</BODY>

</HTML>


