<H1><CENTER>THE NORTH-SOUTH CENTRE</CENTER></H1>

<H3><CENTER>The European Centre for Global Interdependence and Solidarity</CENTER></H3>

<H1><CENTER> Council of Europe</CENTER></H1>
<HR WIDTH=75% ALIGN=center><BR>
<BR>
<BR>

<H2>Welcome</H2>

Welcome to the home page of the North-South Centre of the Council of Europe.
The aim of this page is to introduce you to the work of the North-South Centre
as well as the keep you up to date on our programme of activities.
Furthermore it will give you online access to our two  monthly publications:
The Interdependent (both in English and French) as well as "Terra Viva" 
(English only for the moment), as well as provide you with a link to
 <A HREF="medhome.htm">MedGate</A>:  a network of organisations
 working on Trans-Mediterranean Cooperation and  Partnership.
 <P>
In the furure we hope to provide elaborate links to pages of other organisations working
in the field of North-South Interdependence and Solidarity or other related fields such as<STRONG> environment,
human rights, etc</STRONG>. Please<A HREF="#mail"> mail</A> us
any links you consider interesting, as well as any comments you
would like to make on these pages<P>

<H2>The North-South Centre</H2>

The North-South Centre, also known by its full name "The European Centre for Global
 Interdependence and Solidarity" is a partial agreement within the wider structure of the
<A HREF="coeinfo.htm"> Council of Europe</A>. Bla Bla Bla.........
<A HREF="nsinfo.htm"> More information</A> is available in a separate document.<P>
 
<H2>Programme of Activities</H2>

The programe of activities of the Centre consists of three windows. Bla bla bla bal bal bal<P> 

Please consult our<A HREF="calendar.htm"> calendar</A> for more information on the current activities 
of the North-South Centre<P>

