<body>

<center><p>
<hr width="100%" ><font COLOR="#000080"><font SIZE=+3>REGIONAL SEMINAR
ON THE</font></font></p></center>

<center><p><b><font COLOR="#000080"><font SIZE=+3>CHEMICAL WEAPONS CONVENTION</font></font></b></p></center>

<center><p><font COLOR="#000080"><font SIZE=+3>AND ITS NATIONAL IMPLEMENTATION
</font></font>
<hr width="100%" ></p></center>

<center><p><font COLOR="#95004A"><font SIZE=+2>12 - 14 JUNE 1996, MALTA</font></font></p></center>

<center><p><font COLOR="#95004A"><b><tt><font SIZE=+2>OUTLINE OF A TENTATIVE
PROGRAMME</font></tt></b> </font>
<hr width="100%" ></p></center>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>WEDNESDAY, 12 JUNE 1996</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>09.00 Inaugural Session</font></b></p>

<ul>
<p><font SIZE=+1>Chairman and Moderator: </font></p>

<p><font SIZE=+1>Mr. Saviour F. Borg, Director Multilateral Affairs, Ministry
of Foreign Affairs</font></p>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Keynote speech by the Executive Secretary of the Preparatory
Commission, Mr Ian R. Kenyon.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Welcome address by Minister for Gozo, Mr. Anton Tabone.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Opening of the Seminar by H. E. Guido de Marco, Deputy
Prim Minister and Ministar of Foreign Affairs, Malta</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Welcome reception</font></li>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>11:00 Introductory Plenary Session</font></b></p>

<ul>
<li><font SIZE=+1>Background to the Chemical Weapons Convention.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>The work of the Commission until June 1996.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>National statements</font></li>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>13:00 Break</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>14:30 - 18:00 Afternoon session</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>14:30 Legislation required to meet the basic undertakings
under the CWC</font></b></p>

<ul>
<li><font SIZE=+1>Existing Legislations</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>What kind of legislation is required? What are the parameters?</font></li>
</ul>

<p><font SIZE=+1><b>16:00</b> <b>Break</b></font></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>16:30 National Authority under the CWC</font></b></p>

<ul>
<li><font SIZE=+1>Setting up National Authority:</font></li>
</ul>

<ul>
<ul>
<li><font SIZE=+1>defining its area of responsibility,</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>budget for NA&nbsp;and its programme including contribution
to OPCW</font></li>
</ul>

<li><font SIZE=+1>The role of the National Authority (what are the actions
a State Party may entrust to NA?)</font></li>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>THURSDAY, 13 JUNE 1996</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+2>09:00 - 12:30 Morning Session</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>09:00 National Authority under the CWC&nbsp;(continued)</font></b></p>

<ul>
<p><font SIZE=+1>Moderator:</font></p>
</ul>

<ul>
<li><font SIZE=+1>Training of National Authority personnel</font></li>

<ul>
<li><font SIZE=+1>officers of NA</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>NA&nbsp;escort team</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>the role of the PTS&nbsp;in such a training</font></li>
</ul>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Communications with OPCW</font></li>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>10:30 Break</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>11:00 Declaration and Inspection issuess</font></b></p>

<ul>
<li><font SIZE=+1>Identification of declarable activities and facilities</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>National preparations for receiving inspections</font></li>

<ul>
<li><font SIZE=+1>industry inspections</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>challenge inspections</font></li>
</ul>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Operational tasks relating to declarations</font></li>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>12:30 Break</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>14:30 - 18:00 Afternoon Session</font></b></p>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>14:30 Issues relating to trade in scheduled chemicals</font></b></p>

<ul>
<p><font SIZE=+1>Moderator:</font></p>

<li><font SIZE=+1>The legal framework for collecting import/export data.
National examples.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>The role of the customs authorities in data collection.</font></li>

<li><font SIZE=+1>Transhipments of scheduled chemicals - political and
practical impact.</font></li>
</ul>

<p><b><font SIZE=+1>20:00 Reception hosted by Minister for Gozo, Mr. Anton
Tabone.</font></b></p>

